title: spiced french toast
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow dish, stirring well. Coat a large, nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Dip bread slices, 1 at a time, into egg mixture, coating well.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries, then put them through a food grinder.
Put unpeeled orange through the grinder.
Add sugar to this cranberry and orange mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and chill. When mixture is slightly thickened, fold in the cranberry and orange mixture.
Pour into molds and chill firm.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine, water and oil; mix well.
Add 1/2 of condensed milk and blend.
Pour half batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt and blend together caramels and remaining milk.
Spread over baked cake and sprinkle with pecans.
Pour remaining cake batter over caramel. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: baked beans
directions: Rinse dry beans in cold water.
Then soak for 1/2 hour in boiling water.
Drain and put in covered baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 450° for 4 hours or until tender.
Add hot water as needed to avoid cracking glass dish. You can also add bacon or onion to taste.

title: rum chocolate mousse
directions: Cook the sugar in the rum over a very low heat until it's dissolved.
Melt the chocolate in a double boiler.
Then stir in 2 tablespoons of cream.
Add rum syrup and stir until smooth.
When cooled, fold in the egg whites.
Whip the 2 cups cream and fold it gently into the chocolate mixture.
Chill in 8 to 10 glasses at least 2 hours before serving.

title: grandma's tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped onion and bell pepper.
Drain and add tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, corn and chopped olives.
Simmer.

title: fresh apple squares
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil together until well blended.
Stir together dry ingredients and fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool dust with confectioners sugar and serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Chill in freezer before baking.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown meat, then put a spoonful or two of meat and a few chopped onions in the center of each tortilla and roll up.
Melt other ingredients together and pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Partially thaw bread dough.
Break one loaf into 1-inch pieces and place scattered in greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Melt margarine, stir in pudding, brown sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Pour over broken bread pieces.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix apricot preserves, soup mix and salad dressing together. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Saute chicken in hot oil 5 minutes each side.
Add pea pods, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cook uncovered for 7 minutes. Stir often.
Season with all seasons; thicken chicken broth with cornstarch.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until thickened. Sprinkle top with fresh cut green onions or slivered almonds. Serve with rice.

title: apple scrunch
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan, then pour into a bowl.
Pour pie filling into pan; sprinkle dry cake mix over it, then pecans. Drizzle melted butter over all of it.
Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli for 2 minutes.
Mix soup, onion, mayonnaise and cheese together and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry lemon bread
directions: In a bowl, combine well the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
In a large bowl, stir together the shortening and the sugar; add the eggs and combine the mixture well.
Stir in the buttermilk, vanilla and rind, combining the mixture well.
Add the flour mixture and stir the batter until it is just combined.
Stir in the cranberries gently and pour batter into buttered loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until skewer comes out clean.
Cool on pan on rack for 10 minutes.
May be wrapped tightly in foil and frozen.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Cut in shortening.
Mix well.
Beat egg in measuring cup.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Fill cup until 3/4 full of cold water.
Mix into dry ingredients. Makes 2 to 3 shells.

title: monkey bread(kids of all ages love this!)
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Mix 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Cut biscuits in quarters and shake in plastic bag. Place half the biscuits in pan.
Boil 1 cup sugar and butter or margarine.
Pour half over biscuits in pan.
Place remaining biscuits in pan and pour other half of butter-sugar mixture over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This may be runny; place foil under pan.

title: grandma miller's potato salad
directions: Mix these together and add the dressing while warm.

title: london broil teriyaki
directions: Start grill.
Make teriyaki sauce:
In a small saucepan combine the soy sauce, oil, apricot jam, cornstarch, pepper and whole garlic cloves.
Stir to blend.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Brush steak with sauce. Grill 4 inches from heat turning once; brush the second side with sauce.
Grill 5 to 7 minutes per side for rare, 8 to 10 minutes per side for medium-rare, 11 to 13 minutes per side for well-done.

title: basic cookie recipe
directions: Mix together the softened shortening, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg. Add flour, salt and soda; mix thoroughly.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat to boiling point the water and butter. Add (all at once) and mix well the flour.
Dough will form a stiff ball. Remove pan from heat. Add eggs (one at
a time), beating each egg into mixture until smooth and satiny.

Using a tablespoon, put spoonfuls onto a well-greased baking sheet, leaving enough space for puffs to grow up and out. Total baking time 45 minutes; first 10 to 15 minutes at 500°, last 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove puffs from oven and let cool slowly on countertop, out of any drafts. When cool, using sharp knife, cut tops off and lay them aside. Using a fork, gently remove the soft insides of each puff.
Fill puffs with Cool Whip (or cold custard or ice cream).
Replace tops.
Spread chocolate frosting on top of each cream puff and refrigerate until eaten.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in a dry place.
Add hot water to make drink.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in marshmallows and 2 1/2 cups apricot nectar.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; chill and let set.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or several hours in crock-pot.
Great at parties served with toothpicks.

title: cheddar spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended using an electric mixer.
Place in an airtight container and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend. Store in refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature 20 to 30 minutes or until softened.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: texas cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the flour, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil in small saucepan the margarine, water and cocoa. Add to flour mixture and stir well. Beat eggs well and add. Combine soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Add and mix well. Pour into greased and cocoa covered jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown beef in olive oil; drain all fat and place in a saucepan.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil; add to saucepan.
Add Italian seasoning, tomato sauce, tomato paste, tomatoes and basil leaves to mixture.
Bring to a boil. Cut heat to low and cook 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Layer noodles, meat sauce and cottage cheese.
Put Mozzarella on top and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: Cook bacon, drain drippings, all but 2 tablespoons.
Add onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Add enough water to broth to make 2 1/2 cups.
Pour into skillet and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, bacon, thyme and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper.
Cover and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in beans.
Let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed.

title: wok lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or just tender.
Drain lasagna or noodles and set aside.
In medium mixing bowl stir together the cottage cheese, cream cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Set aside.
Preheat work or large skillet over high heat.
Break up meat.
Stir-fry meat and garlic for 2 or 3 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and cooked noodles.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over mixture in wok. Sprinkle with Mozzarella, then Parmesan cheese.
Reduce heat. Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and chop coarsely.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Scrape into 1-quart baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered, or until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serve hot or cold with crackers.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line a 7 1/2 x 12-inch Pyrex pan with whole graham crackers. Make pudding as directed on box; pour over crackers.
Layer 1/2-inch of Cool Whip, then place another layer of crackers on cream.
Press together.
Cover with butter icing (thin layer). Melt chocolate chips with oil and drizzle over icing.
Let stand overnight.

title: coffee cake
directions: In small bowl, make filling by combining nuts, sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, pudding, oil, sour cream, eggs and vanilla; mix well.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix well. Blend cream cheese, remaining sugar, Dream Whip and milk.
Spread half the crumb mixture in oblong dish.
Add half the cream cheese mixture.
Spread pie filling on top.
Add remaining cheese mixture; top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours before serving (until firm).

title: black cat cupcakes(makes 24 cupcakes)
directions: Coarsely chop 14 cookies.
Prepare cake mix batter according to package directions.
Stir in chopped cookies.
Spoon batter into 24 paper lined 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from pans; cool on wire rack.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well and heat over low heat.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered cake pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon into prepared pan. Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl; beat until smooth. Spoon evenly over cake, leaving 1-inch edge.
Bake for 50 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Invert squares on serving plates. Makes 20 servings in pan size 9 x 13-inch.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and let cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, cranberry sauce, celery and pecans.
Put into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan or your favorite mold, sprayed lightly with cooking spray.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce lined plate.
Serves 12.

title: pork loin with pineapple
directions: Scrape surface of pork loin.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place in oven roasting pan.

title: no bake butterscotch cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes until soft ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Add pudding mix (dry) and peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in oatmeal and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and allow to cool until firm, about 30 cookies.

title: meaty spinach manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk. Bring to boil, cook and stir 2 minutes until thickened.
Stir in Parmesan cheese until melted, set aside.

title: m&m pistachio squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 9 x 12-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine pudding mix, flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat oil with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
(Alex prefers these squares to be green so I add a few drops of green food coloring.) Pour oil mixture into flour and stir well.
Add M&M candies to batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of
margarine in saucepan; add flour and stir over heat until golden brown; set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine separately; saute green peppers, onions and celery until tender.
Add tomatoes, stock, salt, pepper and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Gradually stir in the flour mixture, stirring until well blended.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add seafood and file; simmer 15 minutes more.
Served over rice is nice!
Serves 12 to 15.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli and rice. Saute pepper, onion and celery. Mix all ingredients. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a large casserole or baking dish, place dry Rice-A-Roni. Top with pork chops.
Place onion on pork chops.
Sprinkle with seasoning mix from Rice-A-Roni.
Mix soup with water and pour over all.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until the rice is done and water is absorbed, about 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir buttermilk into yeast mixture and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a large bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender evenly.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a baking sheet that has been coated with cooking spray.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: low-fat broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
In large bowl, combine broccoli with the egg substitute, soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and pepper and mix well.
Coat a 2-quart casserole dish with Pam and pour in mixture.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Contains 145 calories, 2 grams of fat.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Cook cake in regular sized sheet cake pan.
When cake is done, punch holes in top with a fork.
(Leave cake in pan.)
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over entire cake and let set for about 15 to 30 minutes.
Pour juice off of strawberries over cake and let set 15 to 30 minutes.
After liquids soak into cake, pour strawberries on top and spread evenly.
Then cover entirely with Cool Whip. Garnish with a few sliced strawberries.
Cover pan and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Add butter/egg mixture to flour mixture and mix well.
Add by fourths, 1 quart buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly until all dry ingredients are moist.
Grease and flour large Dutch oven or aluminum pans.
(Can use Baker's Joy spray.) Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Bread should be brown on top and tester come out dry when tested in the middle.
Cool. Slice and butter.
Great with tea or coffee.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy and well blended.
Spread on platter.
Sprinkle with your choice of veggie, toppings and shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips (plain).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 300° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Add seasonings.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add butter and onions to large pot and cook until tender.
Add flour and stir constantly for 1 minute.
Slowly add 2 cans chicken broth, then 3 cans water.
Add broccoli, then salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour stirring occasionally.
Add Kluski noodles and cook until al dente (approximately 15 minutes). Add 4 to 5 cups milk and the cheese.
Heat through and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to cranberries.
Leave set overnight.
Drain.
Add crushed pineapple, seeded California grapes and small marshmallows.
Add Dream Whip and Jell-O.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: sand tarts
directions: Bake at 325°. Roll or sprinkle powdered sugar over them while still hot.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of ungreased baking dish, round, glass.
Top with chili, onions and green chilies. Spread shredded cheese over this mixture; top with olives.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve sour cream on the side with tortilla chips and corn chips.

title: tempura
directions: Stir together flour and baking powder in a bowl.
Add tamari sauce, water and egg.
Stir until smooth (if too thick, add more liquid).
Pour oil into a large pan or wok heated to 375°.

title: rave-bringing beef ribs(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Score ribs on both sides between bones, or cut all the way through.
Lay ribs in bottom of roasting pan with tight-fitting lid.
Combine coffee, liquid smoke, sugar and Worcestershire; pour over ribs.
Cover and bake in oven 2 hours or until ribs are almost tender.
Remove cover and continue baking until ribs are browned and tender, another 20 minutes or so.
Ribs may be turned over after 10 minutes to brown other side.

title: don farmers fresh apple cake
directions: Combine in bowl or mixer oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together next 5 ingredients into oil and egg mixture. Add apples and nuts and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a buttered and floured 9 to 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove from oven and let rest in pan.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini skillet dish
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add zucchini to
meat and onion. Pour sauce over zucchini and sprinkle
Italian seasoning over sauce.
Add cheese on top.	Cover and cook	over
low heat until zucchini is tender.
A nice, one-dish meal.

title: meat loaf
directions: If you have a slice of salt pork or bacon, it is good to have on the bottom or top.
Bake at 350° or 375° for about an hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine flour and sugar together, blending until no lumps remain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick.
Good on grilled chicken, pork chops and spareribs.

title: ham-chicken bake
directions: Melt stick
of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Beat chicken
breasts
flat with saucer.
Take chicken and roll-up. Wrap
cheese
and
chicken, then wrap ham around.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool and pour over strawberries in the crust.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: celery salad
directions: Blend soup, lemon juice, pickles and dill in a bowl.
Toss with celery, apple, beets and potatoes.
Chill 4 hours or more. Serve on salad greens.

title: risotto with shrimp
directions: Saute onion and peppers in oil.
Add rice; cook over medium heat until tanned; stir constantly.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and broth.
Mix and cover tightly.
Simmer without stirring for 35 to 40 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas.
Mix well.
Cook an additional 5 minutes until shrimp is done.

title: brenda's nachos
directions: Mix in kettle and heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.

title: tuna-cheese swirls casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine tuna, peas, broth and rice.
Pour into prepared dish.
Roll out prepared biscuit dough to 6 x 10-inch. Sprinkle with cheese and roll like a jelly roll. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place on top of casserole. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cheddar breakfast
directions: In heavy skillet, saute apple slices in butter briefly just until apples soften. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cut cheese into small pieces over apples.
Let skillet remain over heat just until cheese begins to melt. Serve over whole wheat toast or with toast on the side.
Makes 2 ample servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 500° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Stir vegetables, chicken and soup in ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Stir remaining ingredients until blended. Pour into pie plate. Bake about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a blender.
Blend 2 minutes on low speed.
Then add mayonnaise.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed. Stir in remaining Bleu cheese.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours. Dressing will keep for 4 or 5 days.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mashin' milkshake(yield: 1 milkshake)
directions: 1. Put all ingredients in a blender.

title: two crust sour cream pie
directions: Put raisins in lower crust before adding filling and have upper crust as loose as possible as the filling swells when baking.
Bake in slow oven.

title: seven layer bars
directions: You will need an aluminum throw away square pan or metal pan.

title: company herb biscuits
directions: Mix butter, dill weed and onion.
Cut each biscuit in half. Roll in mixture and place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
May use onion powder, parsley flakes or Parmesan cheese.
Any mixture is good.

title: smoked turkey wings with honey and sweet potatoes
directions: To Prepare:
Wash turkey wings thoroughly.
Place wings in casserole dish (preferably one with cover).
Before placing wings in dish, cut off wing tips.
Boil the sweet potatoes until nearly done.
Remove from water; set aside until wings are three-quarters done or cooked.
Once wings are placed in dish for cooking, pour honey over all the meat.
Mrs. Dash seasoning is optional; if to be used, sprinkle the seasoning over the meat before pouring the honey over the meat.
Add approximately 3/4 cup water in casserole dish.
Cover and bake in oven of 350°.
Test the wings and when wings are done, place sweet potatoes over meat.
Pour small amount of honey over potatoes.
Squeeze 1/4 piece of lemon over food. Place casserole dish back in oven and bake until honey
is glazed over meat.
Serve.

title: bo pilgrim's chicken chili
directions: In kettle, saute onion and garlic in oil until limp.
Add ground Pilgrim boneless chicken and braise.
Add water and tomato sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, cover and simmer 4 hours (if time permits).
Makes 8 servings of 2/3 cup each.

title: mark's sweet little dogs
directions: Mix hot dogs and other ingredients together in a 2-quart pan. Heat on low until hot dogs are heated through, about 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with 1 cup sugar.
Stir in milk to make batter.
Melt butter in a large, deep Pyrex dish.
Pour batter over melted butter; do not stir.
Pour peaches and 1 cup sugar over batter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
In the process of baking, the batter rises and the peaches sink.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken or ribs
directions: If desired, may add A.1. or Heinz 57 sauce.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Mix softened ice cream and flour. Spoon into 6 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: german bologna salad
directions: Mix together; let stand to blend.
Can use garlic salt.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Roll gingersnaps, add melted butter and pat in a 9-inch pie tin.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Soak gelatin in cold water.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add egg yolks; beat well. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Divide mixture in half.
To one add unsweetened chocolate and vanilla.
Mix and spoon into crust.
Cool remaining half.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat; gradually add remaining sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold into cooled custard and add rum.
Spread over chocolate mixture.
Before serving, cover with sweetened whipped cream.
Garnish with chocolate (grated).

title: hot crab and cheese dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Place into lightly greased 2 cup baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Stir milk and lemon juice together.
Add grapefruit and pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream if desired. A real treat for Floridians!

title: taste of texas pasta and chicken
directions: Combine olive oil, lime juice and red pepper in a large Ziploc baggy.
Shake well; add chicken and marinate for at least 15 minutes.
Cook pasta and drain.
Add butter and lime; toss and keep warm.
Remove chicken from marinade (discard marinade).
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and cook chicken.
Remove chicken; add garlic to skillet and cook until lightly browned.
Add salsa and bring to a boil.
Arrange pasta and chicken on plates; top with salsa mixture.
Garnish with fresh lime slices.
Serves 4.

title: putting on the ritz
directions: Cook milk and dates in saucepan for about 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until spreadable. Add pecans. Spread on crackers. Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes (do not overcook).

title: bakery cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine hot roll mix, yeast and sugar.
Stir in hot water, butter and egg until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured cutting board.
With floured hands, shape dough into a ball.
Knead dough for 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 5 minutes.
Roll dough into a 15 x 10 inch rectangle.

title: "best" holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add 3/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons of sugar, vanilla and nutmeg; beat well. Slowly stir in rum and brandy.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Place chilled mixture in punch bowl.
Gradually stir in cream and milk.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons of sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold whites into chilled mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg as desired.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: greater tater casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes more.

title: spicy tomato mini-loaves
directions: Thoroughly combine corn flakes, 1/2 cup of the soup, onion, egg and horseradish.
Mix in ground beef.
Portion meat mixture into 6 parts; shape into individual loaves.
Place on foil lined baking sheet.
Mix together remaining soup, brown sugar and mustard; spread evenly over meat.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes, or until meat is cooked.
Serve, garnished with parsley, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Layer frozen rolls.
Mix cinnamon with white sugar.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle chopped nuts, brown sugar and dry pudding mix.
Slice and dot butter over rolls.
Cover with cloth.
Place in dry place overnight.
Remove cloth and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: patrick's peanut butter apples
directions: Wash and core apple.
Cut into wedges.
Spread peanut butter on wedges.
Serves 2 children.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients about 24 hours ahead of time.
Serve as a dip or spread on any type of crackers.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Better if sets up for 1 hour.
Great with bagel chips.

title: microwave zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini, but do not peel. Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Place zucchini and water in a deep 2-quart heat resistant, non-metallic casserole. Cover and heat on Full power for 7 minutes or until tender. Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Heat, uncovered, on Full power for an additional 2 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Pour into jars and seal. Process pints for 15 minutes and quarts for 20 minutes at 10 pounds in pressure canner.
Makes 9 pints.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well and put in jars.
Store in refrigerator.
To serve, heat sauce thoroughly.
Cut up wieners and dip into sauce.

title: wild rice and turkey casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Stir in soup.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole; sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper.
Cook until medium done.
Drain grease off.
Combine all ingredients in a deep casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May substitute mushroom and chicken soup and add chopped onions.

title: baked cheese pie
directions: Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Set egg whites aside and beat cheese mixture with rotary beater until smooth.
Fold egg whites into cheese mixture.
Brush a deep 9-inch pie pan with soft butter.
Sprinkle generously with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake the salmon.
Mix together the lemon juice, salt and pepper and add to the salmon.
Add the beaten egg yolks, bread crumbs, melted butter and celery.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and mix lightly.
Pour salmon mixture into greased mold and cover with buttered bread crumbs; set the mold in a pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes; unmold.

title: oatmeal sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars with shortening.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture, then add quick oatmeal.

title: chicken 'n dressing
directions: Prepare a pan of corn bread.
After bread is cooked, crumble in a large container.
Boil hen until tender.
Save broth.
Pour broth over cornbread.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Take chicken off bone and stir into the dressing (I don't put the fat in the dressing).
Taste to see if more sage or salt or pepper is needed. If not, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, and bring to a slow boil on medium heat.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Stir to blend, then drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: crock-pot roast fajitas
directions: Place roast in a crock-pot and sprinkle with seasonings. Let cook for 18 hours on low or 8 hours on high. At last 3 hours, place on top the onions and bell peppers. Use warmed thick tortillas and garnish with your favorite toppings: salsa, guacamole, sour cream, etc.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Will keep in jar in frig for a year.

title: harvest chowder
directions: Simmer onion, carrots, potatoes and water together for about 15 minutes.
Add bouillon, corn (if desired) and cooked bacon. Simmer for about 10 minutes more.
Melt butter in another large saucepan and add flour.
Cook for about 1 minute, then add milk and cheese.
Cook until smooth and thick, then combine with vegetables.
Simmer over low heat until ready to serve.
This can also be put in a crock-pot and simmered on low for several hours after cooking.

title: egg souffle
directions: Cook, crumble and drain sausage; blot with a paper towel. Combine all ingredients and put into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 12 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In a large container, mix tomatoes, tomato paste and sauce. Add peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Cook on low heat until done.
(Best if simmered 6 to 8 hours in a crock-pot.) Feeds a large crowd.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix equal portions sour cream and mayo (start with 4 tablespoons each; add more if needed).
Mix and chill.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Makes own crust.
Grease a pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes by hand. Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°. Insert knife to test for doneness.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and spread over crust. Place fruit on crust and top with Glaze.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Place flour on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring every 7 minutes or until flour is brown (color of pecan shells).
Works well in toaster oven.
While flour is browning, coat a large pot with nonstick cooking spray and saute garlic, onions, bell peppers, celery and parsley until tender. Gradually stir in browned flour (roux).
Gradually add water, tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and cook for 15 minutes.
Add crabmeat, shrimp and fish, cooking another 20 minutes.
Add green onions, cooking until all seafood is done. Discard bay leaf and cloves before serving; serve over rice. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas, then dissolve scant teaspoon soda in them. Well cream sugar with shortening.
Then add well beaten egg.
Mix all well and add last 2 scant cups of flour, salt and baking powder.
Bake at 350° until "cake tests" done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cream oleo; add Romano cheese, onion, sharp cheese and stuffing.
Mix well.
Add eggs. Squeeze spinach dry and chop some more.
Mix the spinach and oleo mixture together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze until ready to use or use immediately.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon raspberry muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients stirring just until moistened.
Place paper baking cups in muffin pans and coat with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into paper cups filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° 20 to 22 minutes. Remove from pans immediately.
Makes 36 mini muffins.

title: port wine molded salad
directions: Drain and save pear juice liquid.
Measure and add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat.
Add jello and stir until melted. Add remaining ingredients, except pears.
Add pears when slightly thickened.
If made in a pan and cut into squares, this will easily serve 12 or more.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix Karo and sugar together and heat to almost boiling point. Then add peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press into 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Cool.
Fill pie plate with softened ice cream. Top with small amount of Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Freeze. Cool a few minutes in warm water before cutting.

title: hoosier pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter.
Beat in sugar gradually. Then add eggs, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and bourbon.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. The amount of spice may be adjusted to taste.
To serve hot tea, mix 2 heaping spoonfuls of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add 1/2 cup milk,
flour and 1/2 cup milk.
Add flavorings and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Put in cold oven.
Bake in tube pan.

title: hot and spicy macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package, except using 1/2 cup milk.
Saute red pepper flakes and green peppers in margarine until tender.
Add vegetables and ham to dinner.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pate gourmet
directions: In large skillet, melt 1/2 the salted butter; in it, saute the onion over moderate heat for about 8 minutes, or until soft and transparent but not brown.
Transfer to Cuisinart.
In same skillet, melt remaining salted butter.
Add chicken livers; cook over quite high heat for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring and tossing the chicken livers almost constantly, until they are brown on outside but still slightly pink within.
Pour cognac over them, ignite and let the flame burn out.

title: united airlines nut cake
directions: Combine corn oil, sugar, eggs, flour, carrots, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice, vanilla, cornstarch and nuts.
Mix until blended.
Turn batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool, then frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in the order listed.
Spread the mayonnaise over top of layered ingredients.
Sprinkle the sugar over mayonnaise.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serves 16.

title: swedish christmas bread
directions: Mix yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Melt butter, add stout and heat until lukewarm.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add molasses and half of flour; mix well.
Add yeast, salt, orange peels, fennel seed and some flour, gradually, leaving one cup of white flour. Beat well until dough is smooth and firm.
Cover with a clean towel and allow to rise in a warm place until almost doubled in bulk.

title: creamed roman bean soup
directions: Wash beans and cook with ham hocks in 3 qts. of water. When beans are done, mix flour with small amount of water into a smooth paste. Add sour cream and milk; mix well. Add to the bean soup. Add vinegar and cook until soup comes to a full boil. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: peggy's layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in order given. Mix the mayonnaise, and sugar. Spread on top of layered salad. Sprinkle grated cheese and crumbled bacon on top.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Chill evaporated milk thoroughly. Whip at high speed.
As milk thickens, gradually add sugar.
Add Kool-Aid and mix thoroughly. Spoon into pie shells.
Add whipped topping and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: peppy peppers
directions: Pour dressing over peppers in large bowl.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 6 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve.

title: cranberry  salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and lemon. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Let cool. Add sugar, nuts and celery to cranberries, orange and lemon. Mix well, then add Jell-O.
Better if made 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: philly 15 minute cheesecake(diet)
directions: Combine cream cheese and Equal, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in pineapple and vanilla; pour over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 250° and continue baking for 35 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sour cream pineapple coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, the 1/4 cup pineapple juice, crushed pineapple and sour cream. Mix well and turn into a well greased tube pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 55-60 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and drizzle with a mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar and 2 tbsp. pineapple juice. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Layer tamales and corn in casserole dish.
Pour hot tamale juice over this.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Last 5 minutes, top with cheese and melt.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs; mix in shortening and 2/3 cup of water.
Stir in pumpkin pie filling, salt and spices.
Stir this in pumpkin mixture, using wire whisk. Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 65 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on racks in pans.
Remove when cool.
Serves 6.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bones from salmon.
Add all ingredients, except egg white.
Beat the egg white until stiff and fold into the salmon mixture carefully.
Place in buttered loaf pan and bake in a moderate oven (300°) until brown.
Serve with cream of mushroom sauce made by heating 1 can of mushroom soup and adding 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients and then beat in 2 whole eggs.
At low speed, add 1/4 cup of milk.
At same speed, add 12 ounces of melted butter.
Gently fold in 1 pound of well drained blueberries.
Grease and flour your muffin tins or use paper liners.
Then scoop 2 ounces of mix into each tin or liner and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and line it with dried beef, torn apart. Place chicken breasts on dried beef; place 2 strips of bacon on each breast. Combine sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken breasts. Bake 3 hours in all. Bake, covered, 2 hours and uncovered 1 hour at 275°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar until well blended.
Blend in syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered dip
directions: Spread 2 cans bean dip in a 10 x 13-inch pan or Tupperware dish.
Mix the mayonnaise, taco seasoning mix and sour cream; spread on bean dip.
Spread the avocado dip, then layer green onions on top, then layer tomatoes, black olives and shredded cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: smoky bacon burgers
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion, salt, black pepper and liquid smoke, blending well.
Divide into quarters.
Shape into patty.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each patty.
Hold with a toothpick.
Place burgers on oiled broiler rack.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from source of heat for 5 to 8 minutes on each side or until meat is done. Prepare as regular burgers.

title: tacos
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until browned. Drain excess fat. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 12 tacos.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in oranges and juice.
Bake in 3 round pans (greased, floured or sprayed with cooking spray) at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel balls
directions: Combine caramels, butter and cream; melt in microwave.
Fold in corn flakes and coconut.
This recipe can be doubled for the freezer.

title: mom's lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, mixing well.
Stir in lemon juice and lemon extract.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar on top.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients, then chocolate chunks.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sinful strawberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine jello and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in berries, bananas, pineapple and its liquid and pecans.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set (about 1 hour).
Keep other mixture at room temperature.

title: strawberry coconut divinity(make on a dry day with low humidity)
directions: In a heavy bottom saucepan, combine the sugar, corn syrup and water and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then cover and let boil 3 minutes while the steam washes down any crystals formed on the sides of the pan.
Remove lid and cook to hard ball stage (250° on your candy thermometer).
Stir occasionally while cooking to hard ball stage.
While this is cooking, beat egg whites and combine them with the gelatin in another saucepan; pour the hot syrup in a thin stream into the egg white-gelatin mixture, beating simultaneously.
Mixture will lose gloss and begin to hold shape. Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan. Let cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually add sugar and continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy. By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and nuts. Blend well. Bake in a well greased Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 2 hours. Remove from pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Remove from heat. Stir in granulated sugar and corn syrup, then bourbon.
Combine vanilla wafers and nuts in a bowl and add to chocolate mixture. Form into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
If mixture becomes too hard to handle, soften slightly in double boiler. Yield:
about 60 balls.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion in a skillet until done.
Drain off fat. Add water, ketchup and mustard.
Heat to simmering and add vegetables.
Cover and simmer on low heat until vegetables are done.
Add sour cream and mix through.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over wide cooked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: coriander potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes, cool and quarter. Heat oil in a large saut pan over medium heat. Add potatoes and saut until lightly golden. Add garlic and spices and cook for 3 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add cilantro.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix and pat in a 9 x 12-inch pan oleo, flour, nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° then cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust mixture.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add applesauce, raisins and nuts which have been dredged in 1/4 cup of the measured flour. Sift all dry ingredients together; add to the mixture. Pour into tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours in slow oven at 325°. Ice with Caramel Icing.
Cake keeps a long time. (Notice, no eggs.)

title: rosemarie salad(feed mill)
directions: Whisk together juices, sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Let cool completely and add Cool Whip.
Add cooked pasta, pineapple and oranges, stir to coat and chill until served.

title: molly's punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid as directed; add pineapple juice. Pour into 2 or 3 ice trays. Freeze. Pour remaining punch into container.

title: caramel monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine margarine, brown sugar and water in microwavable dish.
(Can use 2 tablespoons of melted margarine to grease fluted tube pan.)
Cut biscuits in half and roll in cinnamon sugar (1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon).
After syrup is heated thoroughly, put some in tube pan, then some of the biscuits.
Repeat several times.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert on large platter immediately after removing from the oven.

title: fruit whip dip
directions: Cream ingredients together in a bowl.
Add 1/4 cup of orange Tang for flavor or 1 or 2 dashes of your favorite Kool-Aid flavor.

title: cream cheese - chili dip
directions: In saucepan, combine soup and cream cheese.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until blended.
Stir in sour cream, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat through.
Stir in 1 tablespoon water.
Transfer to fondue pot or small chafing dish.
Keep warm over fondue or chafing dish burner.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: highlites cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together.
Add sour cream, eggs, oil and water.
Blend until creamy.
Add chocolate chips and nuts. Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: saucy hot dog pick-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the hot dogs in a quart glass casserole.
Cook covered for about 3 minutes or until the sauce is bubbly.
Stir the hot dogs into sauce.
Cook covered for 2 minutes or until hot dogs are hot.
Serve warm.
Use toothpicks to spear hot dogs.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and cook in water until leaves separate.
Cut off hard part of each cabbage leaf.
Cook rice 10 minutes.
Rinse and drain.
Mix meat, rice, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Put about 2 or 3 tablespoons meat mixture on cabbage leaf.
Roll up and tuck in both ends.
Layer in large cooking pot.
Put tomatoes with juice over cabbage rolls, then sauerkraut, then tomato sauce. Cover all with water.
Sprinkle pepper on top.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook about two hours, until cabbage is tender.
May be frozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll in balls, flatten with fork or glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: puddin's chicken enchilada
directions: Brown chicken; drain fat.
In medium saucepan, combine soups and sauce.
Heat.
Add refried beans and 1/2 cup soup mixture to chicken or until just moist.
Heat thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat mixture in tortillas.
Roll into a burrito. Cover each one with sauce and cheese.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine. Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together 3 sticks margarine, powdered sugar and eggs for 15 minutes.
Spread this mixture over graham cracker mixture.
Drain well the crushed pineapple and layer over mixture.
Layer sliced bananas over pineapple.
Layer Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans or other nuts and chopped maraschino cherries over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: swedish meatballs ii
directions: Combine bread, onion, salt, pepper, nutmeg and milk in large bowl. Let stand 10 minutes; stir in meat until well blended. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls. Brown in butter in large frying pan. Remove with draining spoon and place in baking dish. Blend flour into drippings in pan. Brown lightly. Stir in beef broth, water and milk. Continue cooking until it thickens and makes a thin gravy. Pour over meatballs. Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into 9x13 inch pan and bake at 350° (oven temperatures may vary) for 30-35 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice the tomatoes and place in bowl.
Mix egg, buttermilk, salt and pepper.
Pour over tomatoes.
Keep in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Place enough oil in heavy pot to deep fry tomatoes. Heat the oil.
Pick up each slice of tomato and dredge in flour-corn meal mixture.
Shake off excess.
Deep fry and drain on towels.
Serve hot!

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, and butter; bring to a boil.
Cook for three minutes.
Add vanilla, nuts and popcorn.
Shape into balls when slightly cooled.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease casserole pan and arrange in 2 layers the bread, sausage and cheese.
Then, beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard to eggs and pour over layers.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: italian vegetable medley
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large skillet until tender.
Add zucchini, corn and seasonings; cook over medium heat for 8 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes; cook 4 minutes, stirring often.
Spoon into a serving dish; sprinkle with croutons, if desired, and cheese.
Let stand until cheese melts.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: onion pie(vegetable dish)
directions: Peel and thinly slice onions.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Set aside.
Melt remaining margarine and add to cracker crumbs, press into bottom and sides of pie pan.
Spoon in onions.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake for 30 minutes (until set) at 350°.
This is a great side dish.

title: easy strudel
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie crust.
Add egg yolks, vinegar and water and mix well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Divide dough into 3 parts and work with one at a time.
Roll out on floured cloth, 10 x 15-inch.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, onion and garlic powder.
Drain fat. Cut cheese into small pieces and place in crock-pot.
Add salsa, soup and hamburger mixture.
Turn crock-pot on high.
Stir often until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great for parties.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut vegetables and add dressing.
Let stand in refrigerator while cooking pasta.
Mix drained pasta and cheese with vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup white sugar and place in round cake pan, then bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Upon removal, stir immediately, then let sit and stir again 5 minutes later to completely separate pretzel pieces.
Blend crushed pineapple, cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add pretzels.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water in skins; peel and slice.
Fry bacon crisp; remove and crumble.
Use 2 tablespoons of bacon fat and cook onions until tender.
Add vinegar, bacon, sugar and flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over warm potatoes. Serve hot.

title: low calorie tropical salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss to mix well.
Chill and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: different green beans
directions: Collect early in the morning.
Place in the refrigerator until needed.
Make a heavy
stiff
batter of eggs, flour, milk and a dash of baking soda.
Hold blossoms
side up in one hand, spoon in batter to center of
blossom then fold in petals.
Fry in a frypan of butter turning over to brown on both sides.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix
soup and sour cream.
Crumble crackers into melted oleo and poppy seed.
Layer chicken, soup mixture and crackers into
a 2-quart baking dish, ending with crackers.
Bake until bubbly hot in a 350° oven.

title: arlene's jell-o dessert from missouri
directions: Mix Jell-Os and boiling water.
Mix well and chill.
Stir in pie filling and pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken cutlet casserole
directions: Place cutlets in baking dish.
Cover with rice.
Combine soups and milk until smooth and pourable.
Pour over cutlets and rice.
Sprinkle one envelope of dry onion soup over mixture. Cover.
Cook 1 hour at 350°

title: potato puffs
directions: Beat eggs well; add flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. Fold together, add potatoes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot Crisco; fry until golden brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Bring 8 cups water to boiling.
Add pasta and cook as directed.
Half the pepperoni and add to the pasta.
Stir in pizza sauce, 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms, olives and Parmesan cheese.
Transfer to 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg together.
Pour scalded milk over mixture and beat.
Pour in pie shells.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place pie in oven and turn down to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook the sugar, flour, salt, eggs and milk on medium heat until thick. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and butter. Mix until butter is melted. Add the bananas. Line bowl with vanilla wafers. Pour in half the pudding. Layer vanilla wafers again. Add remaining pudding. Layer vanilla wafers on top.

title: pork spareribs with kraut
directions: Lightly brown spareribs in oil in a hot skillet. Add apples and nutmeg and cook 5 or 10 minutes, until apples are lightly brown. Mix in kraut, caraway seed and brown sugar. Pour apple juice over top; cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: tin can ice cream
directions: You will also need 1 pound coffee can and 3 pound coffee can.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add lemon extract.
Add fruit, nuts and raisins.
Bake in pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grandma's potato cake
directions: This is a very old recipe and didn't include all of the directions that present day recipes do.
Bake at a low temperature for a more moist cake.

title: mccormick chicken and potato bake
directions: Quarter potatoes, with peeling or not.
Wash chicken and potatoes; place in plastic bag.
Shake McCormick seasoning ingredient onto chicken and potatoes while wet.
Arrange in pan and pour 1/2 cup water in bottom of pan.
Close bag with twist tie and punch 4 fork holes in bag.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: "mititei"romanian barbecue sausages
directions: Crush garlic with the salt in water, using a fork.
Add everything else and mix well.
Take approximately 1/4 cup of meat mixture for each sausage and roll between the palms of your hands into a sausage shape about 3 to 4 inches long.
Place sausages side by side into a container.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours, then cook on grill on low fire about 3 minutes on each side until cooked through and browned.
May also be baked in the oven.

title: salmon tomato loaf
directions: Flake salmon and remove bones.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly with 2 forks.
Pour into well-oiled baking dish.
Form in loaf.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dogs and hot peppers
directions: Cut hot peppers in 1 1/2 to 2-inch wide pieces.
Put pieces of hot dogs in these to fit.
Place in pint jars.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over hot dogs and peppers in jars; seal and process in hot water bath for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: parmesan loaves(children's)
directions: Cut French bread in half (lengthwise) and place cut side up on baking sheet.
Spread softened margarine on cut sides.
Bake at 350° until margarine melts.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese in a bowl. Spread carefully on hot bread.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Drain artichokes,
chestnuts, mushrooms, olives.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate several hours ahead of serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumble ground beef into skillet; cook until done.
Drain. Add taco seasoning mix and set aside to cool.
Cut lettuce, celery, tomato and black olives and put into a large bowl.
Top with drained kidney beans, crushed corn chips and shredded cheese. Just before serving, add beef mixture and toss with dressing.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients, adding any or all of the last 4 optional ingredients.
Mix well.
Marinate in refrigerator with enough Sweet and Sour Dressing to blend everything together but don't "drown" it.

title: microwave heath candy
directions: Heat butter and sugar 2 minutes on High; stir.
Cook 8 minutes more to hard crack stage, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread over nuts in buttered pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of syrup and let melt.
Spread over top.
Chill and break in pieces.
(I cook mine in 2-quart glass measuring pitcher.)
Use only real butter, margarine will not work.

title: pork and sauerkraut supper
directions: About 2 3/4 hours before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium high heat, in hot salad oil, cook pork chops until browned on both sides.
Remove chops to plate.
In drippings remaining in skillet over medium heat, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add 1/4 cup apple juice, stirring to loosen brown bits from bottom of skillet.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine onion mixture, sauerkraut, potatoes, apples, brown sugar and remaining apple juice.
Tuck pork chops in sauerkraut mixture, sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Cover baking dish with foil and bake in 350° oven 2 hours or until meat and potatoes are fork tender, occasionally basting meat and potatoes with liquid in baking dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white birthday cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend until smooth.
Makes enough to ice one 2 layer cake.

title: eye of round with dill
directions: Prepare dressing as directed, shake well and pour into marinade dish.
Add rest of ingredients except meat.
Mix well. Place trimmed roast in dish and roll in marinade.
Leave meat in marinade 6 to 7 hours, basting occasionally.
Remove meat and place on rack in roasting pan.
Use meat thermometer.
Cook at 400° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Slice thin to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: goldman's supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli in boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Add cauliflower and boil an additional 5 minutes. Drain.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars, marshmallows and milk in double boiler; cool thoroughly.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into candy mixture.
Pour into prepared crust or graham cracker crust. Refrigerate for a few hours.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in lemon juice, peel and butter.
Add flour and milk.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour into an 8-inch ungreased pan.
Place in larger pan and fill outer pan with boiling water as far up as the batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic chicken(serves 4)
directions: Put oil in shallow dish and coat chicken pieces with it. Cover bottom of a heavy 4-quart casserole with mixture of celery and onion.
Add parsley and tarragon and lay chicken on top.

title: three ingredient pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar and fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill approximately 1 hour.

title: mamaw's crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook all day in crock-pot.
Put in jars while hot and seal.

title: easy toffee
directions: Lay saltine crackers on cookie sheet, overlapping slightly.

title: chili pot pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add the following: chili beans, corn, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Add Ro-Tel according to your taste, and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour into large baking dish and top with a layer of sliced Velveeta cheese.
Top this with Mexican cornbread (mixed according to package directions).
Bake at 400° until cornbread is done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix water and pumpkin, add to sugar mixture.
Mix.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Mix and add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool, then remove.
I have used 4 greased one-pound coffee cans filled 1/2 full, baked for 1 hour.

title: nacho cheese 'n beef soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, brown ground beef and drain.
Add beef broth, picante sauce, cumin and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in soup.
Heat gently, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.
Pour into serving bowls.
Garnish with tortilla chips and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black-eyed pea's baked squash
directions: Cut each squash into 3 or 4 pieces.
Cook in enough boiling water to cover.
Drain in colander and mash.
Combine with rest of ingredients. Cover with light layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: different baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour.
Uncover carefully; bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 1/3 of the cookies into medium crumbs.
Place in bottom of new clay pot or large bowl.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and margarine.
Add confectioners sugar and beat well.
In a bowl mix pudding with milk and let it sit for a couple of minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Combine pudding mixture with cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cookies.
Take the remaining Oreos and crush until they are the consistency of potting soil. Sprinkle over pudding mixture.
Gummy worms or silk flowers may be added for realism.

title: instant hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in airtight container. Serve 2 tablespoons cocoa mix to a mug of hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans.
Form into a ball; roll in pecans.
Serve with favorite crackers, Ritz or Town House or whatever preferred.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat thoroughly and add egg.
Mash banana and add to creamed mixture. Add this to dry ingredients along with milk and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in the 350° oven.

title: holiday date-brandy sauce
directions: Simmer
first
3 ingredients, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat;
add
pecans
and
brandy.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.
Keeps refrigerated several weeks and is good cold too.
To reheat, use double boiler.
It is very thick.

title: busy day cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or top with ice cream, strawberries or any topping of choice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Can use this batter or use any brand cake mix.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Mix together.
Chill 1/2 of mixture in pan with 1/2 of the sour cream spread over it.
Once chilled enough, pour the rest of the mixture in pan and the rest of sour cream spread on top.
Chill 3 hours.

title: dressing
directions: Crumble pan of cornbread in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix together well.
You may need more chicken broth (you can also use broth from a boiled chicken), depending on the amount of cornbread you use.
Pour into greased casserole dish; bake at 375° until done.
Do not let it cook dry.

title: cherry salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, salad dressing, 3 tablespoons of pineapple juice and 4 tablespoons of cherry juice.
Fold in pineapple, cherries, marshmallows and whipped cream.
Add 1/2 cup of nuts.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dice onion and potatoes,
then
place
these along with soup mix, meat, tomatoes and
garlic
powder
in
a large pot. Bring to a boil, then let simmer for at least 90 minutes or in a crock-pot overnight or all
day.
Add cornbread and you have a hot, simple meal.

title: chicken & noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: dilly shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp in cold water, chop finely.
Gradually blend milk and mayonnaise into softened cream cheese and heat until smooth.
Add onions, Accent, salt, dill weed, and Tabasco. Mix well.
Stir in shrimp.
Turn into serving dish and chill until ready to use.
Serve with bagels.

title: "yum-yum" baked fudge cake
directions: Combine in mixing bowl eggs, flour and cocoa. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add butter and nuts and continue to beat about 1 minute. Transfer to lightly greased 8-inch square pan and bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until firm on top. This cake forms a thick fudge sauce in the bottom of pan and cannot be tested with a toothpick insertion.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage.
Add all other ingredients.
Place mixture on crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Add flour, then apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: creamy banana pie(low-fat)
directions: Bake pie crust according to package directions for empty baked crust; cool.
In medium bowl, beat evaporated milk, pudding mix and yogurt until mixture starts to thicken.
Pour half of pudding mixture into cooled crust.
Arrange banana slices over pudding mixture; top with remaining pudding mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Line pie shells with cooked sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour the egg combination over the sausage and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(Freezes beautifully.)

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set in the refrigerator overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Heat water enough to melt shortening. Add shortening. Cool to warm. Add salt, sugar, egg and yeast.
Mix. Add flour and mix. Stir until it draws away from the bowl. Cover to rise.
Punch down and knead lightly; let rise again. Turn out on board and knead until elastic.
Roll out and cut or pinch off in rolls.
I also make cinnamon rolls with this dough. My favorite recipe, also my grandkids.

title: creamy mexican dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cover; chill. Makes 2 cups.

title: pumpkin supreme(serves 15)
directions: Mix crumbs and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add margarine; mix well.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine remaining sugar, cream cheese and eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Pour over crumb crust. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes; cool.
Combine pudding and milk; beat well.
Add pumpkin and spices; blend until smooth and creamy.
Fold in 1 cup whipping topping.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Cover with remaining whipped topping.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the flour, salt, sour cream and raisins.
Add beaten egg yolks; cook slowly until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into an 8-inch cooked pie shell.
Top with whites of eggs (meringue).
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: von's pineapple cookies
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Fold in the Pineapple and Nuts (if desired).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375 for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix wet ingredients.
Blend all together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Fill four 1-pound coffee cans half full (greased well).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When done, let slide out of coffee can and cool on wire rack.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced zucchini and chopped onion in boiling water for 5 minutes. Combine soup and sour cream, stir in shredded carrots; fold in drained zucchini and onion. Mix stuffing and margarine together. Spread 1/2 of stuffing in the bottom of a 12 x 7

1/2 x 2 inch pan or baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 20 minutes or until heated thorough. Can be made with yellow summer squash.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom of pan. Mix cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter over coconut and pecans. Mix together butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Drop this mixture by teaspoon on top of cake batter. DO NOT STIR! As cake bakes, it will envelope this mixture, creating a filling. Bake in 350° preheated oven for approximately 45 minutes. Allow cake to cool in pan before cutting and serving.

title: sweet pepper casserole
directions: Cook peppers until tender, drain. In a bowl mix salt, sugar flour, milk, cheese, and peppers put in a oblong baking dish put crumbled crackers on top and top with cheese bake in a 350° oven just until cheese is melted.

title: d-d's hard candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° (use a candy thermometer) or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring. Pour into lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
(Use hammer over wax paper.)
Shake in bag with xxx sugar.
Store airtight.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Add all ingredients except egg whites; bake in a buttered mold in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Brown chicken over medium heat.
Add seasoning to meat and follow directions on package.
Put chips on microwave-safe plate. Spread chicken over chips.
Pour salsa on the chicken.
Top with the cheese.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted, about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Slice potatoes and place in bottom of lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Slice onions and place on top of potatoes.
Place pork chops on top of that.
Salt and pepper and spread can of undiluted soup over top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: baked peas
directions: Brown bacon; add mushroom soup and peas.
Mix well and pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: christmas bird seed
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Store in airtight container.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a 1
1/2 quart casserole. Cook 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add butter and blend.
Return to microwave and cook 3 minutes or until peanuts are golden brown.
Add soda and vanilla until foaming. Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and store in a airtight container.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Steam vegetables until soft.
In a large sauce pan, heat water and bouillon, on med. heat.
Add milk, bring to a boil and gradually add flour, stirring until thick. Add vegetables and cheese, simmer until cheese melts.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve with raw vegetables such as: carrots, celery, radishes, bell pepper, cauliflower, broccoli and turnips.

title: candy's party casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Drain.
Add cream cheese; stir to melt.
Add corn, pimentos, soup and milk.
Mix with cooked, drained noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a large casserole.

title: red beans and rice
directions: This dish is great with cornbread and slaw!

title: stuffed hens, oriental style
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients except hens.
Toss lightly to mix.
Salt inside of birds, then stuff lightly with mixture.
Truss.
Roast, breast-side up in shallow roasting pan in 375°
oven.
Baste occasionally with melted butter until golden brown and let joints move easily, about 1 1/4 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cranberry sauce and spices. When slightly set, add all other ingredients.
(Other flavors of jello may be used.)

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients except crab and Cheddar, then fold those in.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 15 minutes.
Pour over an 8 ounce bottle shrimp cocktail sauce.
Dip in a variety of crackers.

title: carolyn's dip
directions: Mix.
Fold in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Add broth, garlic, tomatoes and chilies. Bring to a simmer. Lower temperature and add Velveeta. This makes approximately 6 cups of soup at 1 pint per cup.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Stir in nuts and potato sticks (about 1/2 can nuts and 2 small cans potato sticks or more or less, according to your taste).
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes on low heat.
Add oleo and cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls
on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour, salt, shortening, egg yolk and milk.
Mix as for pie crust.
Divide pastry into 2 portions and roll 1/2 to line a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch tray.
Sprinkle about 2 handfuls of corn flakes on pastry.
Spread apple slices on dough.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Roll out other half of dough and place on top of apples.
Brush top with egg white and water mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Remove from oven and while hot, stir well with a wooden spoon. Cool and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat all until smooth. Pour in square pan (8 x 8-inch).
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top and don't stir.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle top with a mixture of 1/2 cup packed brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Heat oven at 375°.
Grease and flour a square pan, 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk; measure flour.
Blend dry ingredients. Stir in.
Spread batter in pan.
Sprinkle with desired topping. Bake 25 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple food cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add liquid shortening and mix with spoon.
Beat eggs. Add sugar and vanilla.
Add sugar mixture to the flour, etc. and mix together by hand, if necessary.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Use ungreased tube pan.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix together butter, cream cheese and extract.
Gradually mix in powdered sugar; mixture will be stiff.
Add food coloring, if desired, and mix until color is evenly distributed.
Can be formed into balls and pressed with fork or formed into balls, rolled in sugar and pressed into molds.
If pressed into molds, freeze for 5 to 10 minutes before unmolding.
These are great for baby or bridal showers.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs (one at a time) and milk. Beat well.
Add flour, corn meal and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: microwave vegetables
directions: Clean and prepare fresh vegetables.
Use frozen ones right out of the bag.
Place in a microwavable cooking bowl.
Lightly salt and pepper, then sprinkle the vegetables liberally with water. Cover and microwave, cooking in 4-minute amounts.
At the end of each time period, stir the vegetables and make sure they are not drying out.
If they are, sprinkle with a little more water. Vegetables are done when they are tender-crisp.
This is an extremely healthy way to eat them.

title: nut bread
directions: Add in order and mix in mixer.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook linguini; drain.
Warm milk and butter.
Mix in sour cream, garlic, cheese and parsley.
Serve over linguini.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice
lemons
as thin as paper, rind and all.	Combine lemons with
sugar.
Let
stand at least 2 hours or preferably overnight. Stir
occasionally.
Add	beaten	eggs
to
lemon mixture;
mix well.
Pour
into
pie
shell,
arranging lemon slices evenly. Top
with
top crust.
Cut slits in crust near center.
Bake
in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and
bake about 20 minutes more until knife inserted near edge
comes
out	clean. Cool before serving.
Very different but very delicious.

title: corn pudding
