directions: Mix cornstarch, eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Add milk and corn. Pour into baking dish.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sue's kentucky chicken
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Sprinkle chicken with Lawry's and garlic salt.
In a bowl mix 16 ounces sour cream and the can of Durkee onions.
Spread sour cream and onion mixture over chicken. Crunch the stuffing and cover the chicken with it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: italian sausage rigatoni
directions: Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place Italian sausages in pan.
Pour 1 tablespoon water over each sausage.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 14 to 16 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove from pan.
Cut cooked sausage diagonally into 1-inch pieces and set aside.
In saucepan, cook oil, garlic and onion over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in sausage, spaghetti sauce, wine, basil and cheese.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Place hot rigatoni on serving plate and top with cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: easy homemade chili
directions: In large saucepan, mix chili seasoning and tomato paste.
Add ground beef and beans.
Stir well.
Add water to desired thickness.
Cook on medium heat until simmers.
Lower heat and simmer 1 hour or until desired flavor.

title: chicken fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt over heat the margarine, half and half, Romano and Parmesan cheeses and spices.
Boil fettucine according to instructions.
Cook chicken in skillet in tablespoon oil.
Add chicken to cheese, pour over noodles.

title: lemon cups
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, and butter; add lemon juice and rind.
Add to combined egg yolks and milk; mix well.
Fold in whites and pour into greased custard cups.
Bake in a pan of hot water in moderate oven (325°) for 45 minutes.
Can be baked in greased shallow baking dish.
Serves 8.

title: easy penne
directions: In a large pot, bring salted water to a boil.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of olive oil, then cook noodles until done, approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
While noodles are boiling, in a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add the sausage and fry until done.
Spoon off any fat drippings and discard.
Add paste and sauce to sausage mixture.
Lower heat and simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Strain noodles and rinse in cold water as soon as they're done.
Toss everything together.
Serve with Parmesan, Cabernet Sauvignon and Italian bread.
Serves 4.

title: soft chocolate cookies
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in sugar; add chocolate and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients with sour cream and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: glorious mess
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add stewed tomatoes and cook until reduced.
Heat beans.
Serve by placing Fritos on plate. Put meat mixture on top; add cheese, then beans and top with lettuce and tomato.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick, season with salt and pepper. Coat both sides with corn meal.
In a large skillet, heat enough bacon drippings to fry tomatoes.
Fry until browned on both sides.

title: frozen tokay mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water.
Blend gelatin into mayonnaise.
Combine fruits.
Fold in mayonnaise, whipped cream, almonds and lemon juice.
Turn into a 6-cup mold, refrigerator trays or pineapple cans.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: hot chicken supper salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese, bread cubes and potato chips.
Pile into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread cubes, potato chips and cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: turtle soup
directions: Boil meat until tender; save liquid for soup.

title: five hour stew
directions: In covered Dutch oven pan, combine meat, potatoes, carrots, onions, tomatoes, salt, sugar, tapioca and red wine.
Place in 300° oven with lid on for 5 hours.
Do not stir.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in nuts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks softened margarine, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs; beat for 15 minutes.
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Layer with sliced bananas, then pineapple and then Cool Whip.
Top with chopped nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: famous five egg sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs on high speed until foamy, about 5 minutes. Gradually add sugar and beat 5 more minutes, at lower speed.
Add lemon extract,
Alternate flour and baking powder with warm milk. Beat 5 more minutes.
Put in ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 50 - 60 minutes.

title: one meal chicken casserole
directions: In 13 x 2-inch baking dish, combine soups, sour cream, broth, onion, mushrooms and seasons.
Arrange breast of chicken on top of sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Garnish with parsley. Serves 6 to 8.

title: trifle
directions: Whip whipping cream.
Mix sugar, sour cream, cream cheese, vanilla and almond extract.
Add whipping cream to this.

title: eggrolls
directions: Brown chicken in oil in skillet; add remaining ingredients except wrappers.
Cook 5 minutes. Drain juice off mixture.

title: crisco icing
directions: Mix all together; beat until creamy.

title: french crepes
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Pour batter into warmed skillet, just enough to thinly cover bottom of pan.
Cook over medium heat until golden.
Fill with fruit, roll up lengthwise and top with whipped cream and powdered sugar.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water; pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place a piece of butter on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Prepare corn according to package directions.
Drain and stir in cream cheese and margarine until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cappuccino mix(low sugar)
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Place in an airtight plastic or glass container. Use 1/4 cup of mix per 8 ounce mug.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and melted margarine.
Add milk, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven back to 300° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie, 10 to 12 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on wire rack.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bring peaches to a boil.
In a large Pyrex dish layer 1/2 of peach slices, then cover with half of cake mix.
Cover mix with remaining peach slices.
Cover with remaining cake mix.
Top cake mix with butter and sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Gradually add sugar to creamed shortening and whip until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture, nuts and lemon rind and blend well.
Add bananas and blend only about 30 seconds.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch) and bake until brown (350° oven for 55 minutes).
Turn on rack and cool well.

title: seasoned burgers
directions: Crush cereal. Mix all ingredients. Shape mixture into 6 patties, each about 3-inches in diameter and 3/4-inch thick. Cook patties in 10-inch skillet over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until no longer pink in center and juice is clear. Makes 6 servings.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in top of double boiler and stir until mixture is thickened.
This makes about 2 cups.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Grind up leftover meat.
Mix meat, onion and Miracle Whip and make up into oblong shape, putting 1/4 pickled jalapeno pepper on one side.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook onions in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add the potatoes, stirring constantly, for about 2 minutes; do not boil.
Top with crumbled bacon and parsley.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add heavy cream and heat.
Add sour cream; stir.
Keep heat low; don't boil.
Add the drained fettuccini, Parmesan cheese, chives, salt and pepper.
Mix gently until well combined.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces, add grapes, water chestnuts, almonds and bacon.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, salt, mustard and curry powder.
Pour dressing over chicken mixture. Serve chilled.

title: million-dollar fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar, butter and salt in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Stir and boil 7 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Pour boiling milk mixture over all and beat until fudge is creamy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan to cool.
Cut into squares when cold.

title: marinated salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix with vegetables, dill weed, garlic salt and Italian dressing.
Add these ingredients in desired amounts according to taste:
fresh mushrooms, black olives, chopped green pepper and sliced pepperoni. Mix and store in refrigerator at least 8 hours before serving.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Chop up bacon and fry; remove bacon.
Add other ingredients to beaten egg.
Mix well and pour into hot fat.
Cook until thick. Serve over lettuce, endive or cooked, cubed potatoes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Dip in egg. Dredge with flour and brown in hot oil.
Drain well on paper towels.
Place a layer of eggplant in a deep casserole. Cover with sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and add
a layer of Mozzarella.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve very hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Peel potatoes and cut into slices 4-inches long and about 1/4-inch wide. Place in a bowl of iced water to crisp. Just before cooking, turn onto paper towel and pat dry. Turn pieces into a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with vegetable oil. Shake pan to spread oil evenly over potatoes and spread into one layer. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, turning frequently, until golden brown. Turn potatoes onto paper towel. Sprinkle with paprika and salt, if desired.

title: dream bars
directions: Place one layer of whole graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Melt margarine, add sugar, milk and egg. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread
half of mixture over graham crackers in dish, then top with another layer of graham crackers.
Spread remaining mixture over graham crackers, then top with another layer of crackers.
Frost with: 1/2 stick melted margarine, 2 cups powdered sugar and enough evaporated milk to blend.

title: bohemian nut slices
directions: Sprinkle yeast and sugar in warm water.
Let stand
10 minutes.
Sift together flour and salt.
Cut oleo in until it resembles coarse meal.
Blend in egg yolks and yeast.
Mix until a small ball is formed.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Beat in sugar (1/2 cup) until peaked.
Fold in flavoring.
Divide dough in half.
Roll into 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Spread with egg white mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make a 1/2-inch deep cut down the center (lengthwise) of each roll.
Bake at once at 375° for 22 minutes. Sprinkle flavored powdered sugar frosting and nuts on top.

title: ruby lair's pie crust
directions: Mix in order.
Beat or mix by hand or mixer.
Chill in refrigerator about 10 minutes.
This recipe may be doubled for 2 double crust pies.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
In large casserole or Dutch oven, mix hamburger and gravy to make bottom layer.
Next layer the corn.
Follow directions for mashed potatoes for top layer. Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted and potatoes golden brown.

title: chili chicken
directions: Mix chicken and tomato sauce in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chili powder, beans and corn.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.

title: exquisite chocolate mint squares
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together over hot water.
Mix thoroughly and drizzle over the cool, firm filling.
Tilt cake back and forth until glaze covers surface.
Refrigerate for at least 5 minutes.

title: kooky cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in bowl and stir to blend together. Make 3 wells in dry mix.
Put oil in one, vanilla in one and vinegar in last well.
Pour water over all.
Stir to mix well. Mixer not needed.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: Combine cheese, margarine and milk at medium speed in mixer until well blended.
Add combined potato chips and flour.
Mix well.
Shape teaspoons and flour.
Mix well.
Shape teaspoonfuls into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375°
for 12 to 14 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes and mix everything together in blender.
Mix on chop and refrigerate if desired for at least 1 hour.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Go by directions on the cake box.
Bake in layers or long cake pan.
Cool cake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheets to 375°.
Peel potatoes and boil them.
Mix potatoes until creamy.
Add butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt and milk.
Stir in coconut and raisins to taste.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Season to taste.
Drain off fat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and beans.
Pour in casserole dish. Mix dry cornbread mix and cream-style corn.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake until cornbread is done.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: black russian cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Add the envelope of noodle soup and rice to the boiling water. Cook for 30 minutes.
In the meantime, cook the sausage.
Remove the sausage from the skillet and then cook the onions and green pepper.
Mix the cooked rice, sausage, vegetables and almonds together in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (This casserole freezes well.)

title: pistachio nut pudding cake
directions: Blend cake mix, 1 box pistachio pudding, oil, orange juice, water and eggs.
Spray angel food cake pan; pour 2/3 of batter into pan and fold into remaining batter the 2/3 cup chocolate syrup. Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease, add other ingredients and simmer for two hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust; put in freezer.
Freeze good. Then put chocolate icing on top.
Refreeze.
Put lids on.
Set out about 10 minutes before serving.
Real good and rich.

title: mexican "trash"
directions: In a lidded container, combine all the ingredients and mix well. Marinate several hours or overnight.
Drain before serving. Serve with nacho chips.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add mayonnaise and soup to beaten eggs; beat. Add grated cheese and diced onion. Fold in cooked broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole. Crumble Ritz crackers over top. Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: extra special gingerbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream together margarine, sugars, egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough 1 hour or overnight.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: dinner rolls from grit
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder, buttermilk and sugar.
Add half flour mix to liquid.
Beat well.
Add shortening, mix slightly and add rest of flour mixture.
Tip on floured board, cover with bowl and let rest 10 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and hot water.
Add remaining
ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture boils, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly before using.

title: heirloom overnight chili sauce
directions: Add onions and peppers to large bowl of prepared tomatoes. Stir in salt and let stand overnight.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes in thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter and sprinkle with herbs. Bake potatoes at 425° for about 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 10 minutes until brown and cheese is melted and potatoes are soft.

title: chicken casserole
directions: One young chicken, cut to pieces.
Place in a stew kettle with hot water to cover.
When cooked tender, make a rich cream gravy over meat.
Line a baking dish with pie crust.
Place chicken and gravy in and cover with top crust one-half inch thick.
Cut slit in center.
Dip fingers in flour and neatly crimp the top same as a common pie.
Bake until nicely browned and thoroughly done.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: In a baking dish (1-quart), put a layer of oysters.
Cover with 1/2-inch layer of bread crumbs or crumbled crackers.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Then add another layer of oysters and bread crumbs or crackers until dish is full.
Moisten the whole dish with 1/2 cup oyster juice and 1/2 cup of milk or cream.
Dot with butter.
Bake in quick oven about 30 minutes or until brown at 400°.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Layer green chilies, that have been seeded, on bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Layer with cheese and pour beaten eggs over this.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the food coloring and cocoa; add to the first mixture.
Add salt, flour, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Mix in, but do not beat, the vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: smoked sausage stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add broccoli, pepper, celery, carrots and onion. Stir-fry over moderately high heat for 4 minutes.
Add sausage, tomato and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix hot spinach into cream cheese. Bake in oven at 350° until bubbly. Mix butter and bread crumbs and put on top of spinach and cream cheese. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer until brown.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: pork chops in sour cream gravy
directions: Brown mushrooms in butter in a skillet, then remove from skillet.
Place pork chops in the skillet and brown on both sides. Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms and cover.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Remove chops to a platter and keep warm.
Mix the flour and remaining water and stir into liquid in skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and pour over pork chops.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring just enough with fork to make a soft dough that sticks together.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead lightly 15 times.
Roll and cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch wide sticks.
Place sticks in a bowl of ice water for
30 minutes to crisp.
Drain. Pat dry with paper towels.
Place potato sticks in a plastic bag. Add cooking oil, paprika and salt.
Shake to coat.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Whisk together egg and milk.
In a separate dish combine flour and bread crumbs.
Dip each eggplant slice in egg mixture, then coat with flour mixture.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Layer in baking dish tomato sauce, noodles, eggplant, Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with tomato sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered for about 30 minutes (until bubbly).
Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick. Cook pie crust a little before you put filling in.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk.
Add the hot milk last. Pour into well-greased 6 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: squash pie
directions: Place drained squash in bowl. Add melted butter. Mix well and set aside. In separate bowl, combine sugar and beaten eggs. Stir well. Add squash mixture, flour, vanilla and baking powder. Mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt in double boiler the butter, water and caramels.
Stir until melted.
Add pecan halves and stir.
Spoon out with tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let dry completely.
Melt in double boiler the milk chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip caramel/pecan clusters in chocolate.
Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: molasses cookie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add molasses to egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Then roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mint julep
directions: Get more juice from lemons and limes.
Heat fruit for 20 to 30 seconds on High.
Cut and squeeze out the juice.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Toss together with Zesty Italian dressing all vegetables (optional and others can be added).

title: almond mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve in hot coffee.
Stir in honey and salt.
Chill until jellied.
Add rum.
Whip the cream and fold it into the gelatin mixture.
Pour into refrigerator trays or a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Freeze.
When there is a frosty border of 1-inch around the pans, turn into a mixer bowl and beat smooth. Stir in almonds and re-freeze.
Serve with rum-flavored whipped cream and additional almonds as garnish.

title: aunt lizzie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and nutmeg and add to sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal and raisins and mix well.
Form into small balls, well spaced on greased cookie sheet.
(Cookies will spread.)
Press a raisin on top of each.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks or cutting boards before storing in cookie tins with tight lids.
Makes a lot.

title: chicken 'n chips bake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and pile lightly in small baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until heated thoroughly.

title: mama's cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheet. Bake in 350° oven about 15 minutes or until lightly brown on top. Makes 3 dozen.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic, salt and onion; drain grease.
Add cheeses; heat until melted.
Add sour cream, mushrooms and olives; set aside.
Soften corn tortillas in hot oil; drain.
Fill each tortilla with meat mixture; roll tightly.
Place seam side down on foil lined cookie sheet (spray foil with cooking spray or oil). Top with slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Cover with foil (also sprayed).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes (until cheese on top melts).
Serve with salsa or picante sauce.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; pour salt on top.
Cover with ice and let set 3 hours.
Drain well.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and seasoning; mix well.
Pour over mixture and boil 5 minutes.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: pizza greens
directions: Cook sausage with garlic powder and hot pepper.
Chop to small pieces. Add spinach and simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Roll out bread dough and cut in half. Sprinkle cheese over dough and spread the cooked mixture over this.
Roll it up and put the 2 loaves on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: combination marmalade
directions: Quarter, remove seeds, run through food chopper.
Measure. Place in large pot.
Add 3 cups of water to each cup of pulp. Bring to a boil for 15 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
Measure out 3 cups of stock into large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar and cook rapidly to 220°.
Remove from heat.
Let cool to 190° and pour in clean jars.
Seal at once with self-sealing lids.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add egg yolk and flour.
Mix the dough until stiff.
Shape into log, about 2 x 18-inches.
Refrigerate.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Brush with beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: lemon roasted chicken
directions: Mix mustard and lemon juice in a small bowl. Place chicken on broiler pan. Brush with mustard mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil together; pour over diced apples and nuts. Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over apple mixture.
Mix and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (ovens may vary).

title: country fried steak
directions: Take one sheet pan and sprinkle flour over the bottom of the pan. Pat hamburger meat over the flour until it is flat and then sprinkle flour over the top of the hamburger meat.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste. Cook in a 450° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pop's apple ugly cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Then stir in:

title: apple dip
directions: Microwave cheese until soft; add other ingredients and blend with mixer until smooth.
Serve warm with fresh fruit slices.

title: blue cheese french bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut loaf diagonally into 1-inch slices. Mix butter and Blue cheese; spread half of mixture on bread slices.
Reassemble loaf.
Spread top of loaf with remaining butter mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Wrap loaf in aluminum foil.
Heat for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni-bean salad
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain and cool. Drain beans and combine with macaroni, eggs (diced and chopped) and pickle relish.
Blend Miracle Whip, salt, pepper and sauce. Toss lightly with macaroni mixture.
Chill and serve.
You can add onion to taste.

title: grandma's white salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add undrained pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: lemon-basil mayonnaise
directions: Process mayonnaise and garlic clove in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Add basil and lemon rind; pulse 3 or 4 times or until basil is finely chopped.
Store covered in refrigerator up to 1 week.
Makes 2 cups.
Good with fish.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut tips off squash and cut each squash into 3 to 4 pieces. Drop squash into large saucepan with enough boiling water to cover.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and cook until tender. Drain in colander and mash.

title: apricot delight
directions: Prepare jello and let jell about half-way.
Then stir pineapple, marshmallows and bananas into thickened jello.
Let jell completely.

title: asparagus and mushroom casserole
directions: Place peas and onions in casserole.
Add mushrooms with liquid.
Arrange asparagus in rows on top.
Cover with soup. Place in a 300° oven and bake until soup melts down in casserole. Remove and cover top with cheese and crackers.
Return to oven and bake at 300° until light brown on top.

title: easy chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix according to mix instructions and pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Cool and ice.

title: 1 gallon chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix together all other ingredients, adding water as needed.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cover and boil 1 minute.
Uncover.
Cook at medium, steady boil to soft ball stage in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until mixture is creamy and begins to hold its shape, about 10 minutes.
Mix in fruits and nuts. Pour into greased pan.
When firm, cut into squares.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Place uncooked noodles in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place raw chicken pieces on top of noodles.
Season.
Mix soups and milk together.
Pour over chicken and noodles.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.
May cover with foil but don't peak!

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Roll out 2/3 pastry; fit into 9-inch pie plate.
Mix well sugar, flour, cinnamon and allspice.
Toss with apples.
Layer 1/3 apple mixture, then 1/3 cherries in pastry-lined pan.
Repeat twice.
Dot with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry; place on top of filling.
Trim edges and flute rim; cut vents.
Can be frozen at this point.

title: artichoke stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms by gently wiping them with a damp cloth. Gently twist the stems and remove.
Combine the chopped artichoke hearts, Swiss cheese, stuffing mix and black olives.
Mix well. Stuff the mushrooms with this mixture and place on a baking sheet. Place the pan at least 8 inches away from the broiler unit.
Broil for about 3 minutes or until tops are lightly browned.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Fold into oiled Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk, salt and butter.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon into greased 2-quart shallow dish.

title: carrots
directions: Combine in a saucepan the water, margarine and brown sugar. Bring liquid to a boil.
Add carrots to boiling liquid.
Bring carrots to another boil.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes at medium simmer or until carrots are tender.

title: five pounds chili
directions: To hamburger meat, add remaining ingredients.
Add water as needed.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Peel a cucumber and slice in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Stuff with filling such as chopped shrimp, lobster or crab meat mixed with mayonnaise or cream cheese mixed with Feta cheese. Chill well and serve sliced in bite size pieces.

title: whale luau
directions: Cut whale into 1-inch squares. Takes 4 weeks. Add potatoes and carrots and place in 400-gallon pot. Cook 4 weeks at 350°. Garnish with parsley. Serves 3,700. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter with chocolate pieces.
Add sugar and well-beaten eggs.
Add nuts.
Bake in prepared pie shell at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bread pies
directions: Butter a slice of bread; place on pie iron, buttered side against iron.
Add pie mixture (2 or 3 tablespoons) to center of bread.
Butter second piece of bread and place on iron, buttered side to iron.
Close and lock iron.
Cook on open fire until brown.
Remove from iron; sprinkle with sugar and allow to cool. Be careful to check pie mix, as it becomes very hot and requires extra cooling.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer or hen in water.
Let cool.
In large skillet, melt oleo and brown onions, green onions, peppers, celery and tomato paste.
Cook until tomato paste looks brown.
Add parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in enough chicken broth to make soupy. Add meat from chicken.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 2 minutes with mixer. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Drain 1 large can sliced peaches. Keep the juice. Place peaches over the batter.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in the remainder of ingredients.
Spread 1/4-inch thick on crackers.
Broil approximately 5 minutes.

title: pasta "worma"
directions: Plunge tomatoes into boiling water for ten seconds.
Peel and quarter them.
Heat olive oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and garlic and saute.
Add tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook until liquid has evaporated.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Place pineapple (including juice) in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Add cherries next.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Slice margarine into pats and place on cake mix along with nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until it is lightly browned. Serve with Cool Whip or French vanilla ice cream.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well and add flour, baking powder and salt. Combine remaining sugar, cinnamon and nuts in bowl.
Place 1/3 of batter in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle top with 3/4 of nut mixture. Spoon on remaining batter and top with remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Unfold pie crust and place in pan as directed on back of package. heat oven to 425°. In large bowl, combine all filling ingredients; mix lightly. Prepare pie according to two crust pie. Bake at 425° for 40-45 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Drink.

title: salt risin bread
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Add cornmeal, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Wrap mixture in a heavy cloth.
Cover and allow to stand in a warm place overnight.
Remove potatoes.
Add milk, water, soda, salt and shortening.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to knead until smooth and elastic.
Form dough into 3 loaves.
Place in well-greased pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until done.

title: chilean salad
directions: Mix chopped tomatoes and corn.
Whisk oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper together.
Pour over tomato mixture.
Arrange sliced onion on top.
Garnish with cilantro.
Serves 4.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cut each onion into quarters.
Cut cabbage into 6 wedges. Arrange cabbage and potatoes in shallow 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch casserole or roasting pan.
In a 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook onions until golden brown.
Remove onions to casserole with cabbage.
In oil remaining in skillet, cook pork chops until lightly browned.
Tuck pork chops among vegetables in casserole.
In same skillet, over high heat, heat apple juice, vinegar, pepper and dried fruit, stirring to loosen any brown bits from bottom.
Pour apple-juice mixture over pork chops and vegetables.
Cover casserole and bake in 375° oven 1 to 1 1/4 hours until pork chops and vegetables are fork-tender, basting meat and vegetables with liquid in casserole several times during baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and cook in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blessing pie
directions: Blend whipped topping with crushed pineapple and pudding mix and top with slivered almonds and flaked coconut.
Chill.
Add to already prepared pie crust.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand.
Pour into a 9 X 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine half of the croutons with all the remaining ingredients.
Turn into baking dish and cover with remaining croutons.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May be prepared ahead, but if so, do not put in croutons until baking time.
This is good for a luncheon or light dinner with a congealed or fruit salad and rolls.
Serves 6.
Psalms 103.

title: pearl's meat loaf
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, except for the sausage and ground beef.
Mix the ground beef and sausage together, then add to the first mixture.
Mix well; shape into two 8 x 4-inch loaves. Place in pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: louisiana pie
directions: Combine butter, sugars and salt; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, flour, cream and pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Shake biscuits in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Cook in saucepan, the margarine and brown sugar until melted.
Add pecans.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix broccoli slaw, sunflower seeds, almonds, onion and broken noodles.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar & beef seasoning and pour over broccoli slaw.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt together and carefully blend through the berries.
Pour berries into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust, flute edges and vent top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven heat to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer, or until golden brown.

title: baked beans and wieners
directions: Put pork and beans in baking dish.
Add chopped onion, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Place split wieners on top of beans.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until it is melted.

title: dripless popsicles
directions: Mix together and freeze in ice cube trays or popsicle trays.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan (fill half full).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: papaya banana bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, add bread cubes, milk, egg whites, apple juice concentrate, papaya, bananas, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg, maple syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 8 x 11 x 2-inch ovenproof glass baking dish.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1 cup crushed cornflakes for topping.
Mix well and turn into a buttered casserole dish.
Mix remaining cup of crushed cornflakes with 2 to 3 tablespoons melted butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Better when reheated in microwave next day.

title: grandma's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 6 cups of milk, salt, sugar and cinnamon into pot; cook at low flame.
Meanwhile mix the remaining 2 cups of milk with cornmeal flour.
When previous mix is now boiling, add cornmeal mix vigorously until desired texture.
Remove from flame.
Stir in margarine, then let cool for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to already cooled mix; pour in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool.
Decorate as desired.

title: gingersnap bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In large saucepan, melt shortening.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except 2 tablespoons sugar; mix well.
Press in bottom of prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Cool completely.
Makes 48 bars.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and bananas.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: edna lambert's corn bread
directions: Mix shortening, salt, sugar and egg.
Dump in remaining ingredients.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes (very important).
Bake in greased pan or muffin pan 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add salt, mashed sweet potatoes, milk and vanilla.
Pour in baking dish.
Add topping.

title: golden jubilee punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda, in a gallon jug and freeze. When ready to serve, thaw and add the soda.

title: fishes dipped in six perfumes(the chinese invented this one (it says here).  have fun!)
directions: Moisten fish with lemon juice.
Marinate in enough water to cover along with the onion pulp (you could pulp the onion directly with the water in a blender) for 2 hours.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Dust fish with a little anise or mace, then with cayenne. Dip
in lightly beaten eggs and fry to golden brown in butter. Remove fish to a hot platter.
Add 3 tablespoons butter to marinade and soy sauce in which the cornstarch has been suspended. Simmer until thickened.
Put in fish. Simmer 2 minutes. Remove fish to platter. Serve sauce separately.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together ham, pork sausage, crumbs, and egg. Add enough milk to mixture so that it will roll into small balls. Bring brown sugar, mustard, water, and vinegar to a boil. Pour 3/4 of sauce over ham balls in baking pan.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes. Use remaining sauce to pour over balls when serving. Freezes well.

title: perked punch
directions: Use a 32-cup percolator.
Place juice in coffeepot and add enough water for a full pot.
Place brown sugar and spices in basket.
Plug in, go to the meeting and when you return, your delicious punch is ready.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt oil and chocolate together in microwave.
Mix all remaining ingredients together. Chill for several hours.
Roll in a ball and then roll in powdered sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Continue until gone. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a deep baking pan.
Pour on batter made with the sugar, flour, milk and baking powder. Heat the fruit with the extra sugar.
Pour the hot fruit on top of butter and bake for 25 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with Fritos.

title: key lime pie(one 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixer bowl, combine egg yolks and condensed milk.
Stir in lime and coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared shell.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: kool-aid
directions: Fill container with water.
Add Kool-Aid.
Mix.
Serve chilled for a fun and refreshing drink.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush 1 cup Ritz crackers or similar crackers; combine with 3/4 stick melted margarine.
Spread over top and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: heartrock dressing
directions: Blend cottage cheese and buttermilk in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add dressing powder and continue to blend.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together with mixer. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies(cholesterol free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with wire whisk; set aside.
In large bowl, blend sugar with electric mixer.
Add margarine and mix to form a grainy paste.

title: quick kosher dills
directions: Wash cucumbers, 2 to 4-inches long and place in clean jars. Add 1 clove garlic, pepper and dill.
Bring water, vinegar and salt mixture to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
To seal the jars, process in a boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: irene "connie's" italian love cake recipe
directions: Prepare marble cake mix as directed.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese right on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix the crab and bread crumbs.
Then mix together the next 7 ingredients.
Pour into crab and mix well.
Form into small cakes or place in crab shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil until brown, about 5 minutes.

title: microwave seafood stuffed chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts between 2 pieces of waxed paper until nicely flattened.
Marinate in Italian salad dressing for several hours.
Take chicken from the marinade and salt and pepper to taste.
Place 1/4 cup of crab or diced shrimp in the center of each breast.
Roll up and fasten with a toothpick.
Combine the melted butter with the lemon juice.
Place chicken breasts in a small shallow baking dish and drizzle with the lemon-butter sauce.
Cook at High (100%) for 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken and seafood are thoroughly cooked.
Rotate dish after 4 to 5 minutes of cooking and baste with lemon butter sauce.

title: white chili
directions: Place rinsed beans in large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by at least 3 inches and soak overnight.
Place chicken in large saucepan.
Add cold water to cover and bring to simmer. Cook until tender.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin.
Cut into cubes. Drain beans.
Heat oil in same pot.
Add onions and saute until translucent.
Stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano and cayenne. Saute 2 minutes.
Add beans and stock; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until beans are tender, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours.
Add chicken and 1 cup cheese to chili; stir until cheese melts.
Season with salt and pepper. Ladle into bowls.
Serve with remaining cheese and sour cream.

title: oatmeal chocolate and nut cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add 4 eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and oatmeal.
(Blend and turn oatmeal into powdered; measure first, then blend.)
Add salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix together all ingredients and add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make ball size 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes approximately 110 cookies.

title: the best fried fish ever
directions: In a Ziploc bag, place fillets and add Tabasco sauce according to amount of fish.
Use enough Tabasco sauce as to see visible on fish. Marinate overnight. Take fish out; do not drain off sauce. Batter as you would and fry as usual.
Contrary to belief, the fish is not spicy hot, but has a delicious flavor.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Blend cornstarch and water to make smooth paste.
Stir in soy sauce and sugar.
Slowly stir into broth.
Bring to boil and simmer until clear, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Slowly add eggs, stirring until eggs shred. Add green onions and serve immediately.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.
In bowl, stir together cream cheese, dressing and dill weed.
Spread mixture evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with desired vegetable toppings and shredded cheese.
Gently press vegetables and cheese into cream cheese mixture.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in flour, nuts and chips. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into balls and flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch closely.
Do not overbake.
They should be light brown on bottom.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder; mix well. Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each cup.
Fold in nuts if desired. Pour into greased Bundt pan or two loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Remove and store in covered tin or wrap in foil.
Allow bread to cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 12 servings.

title: moist chicken with mustard
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chicken breasts, then coat with stuffing crumbs.
Lay in baking pan.
Drizzle with mixture of half butter and half lemon juice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, for an additional 15 minutes.

title: canned christmas cake
directions: You will also need 1 1/2-pint straight canning jars.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Saute cashews in 1/8 cup of oil.
Remove from pan.
Saute chicken pieces in deep frying pan.
Add cashews, water chestnuts, mushrooms and chicken broth to frying pan.
Bring to a boil.
Mix 1/4 cup of soy sauce with 2 1/2 tablespoons of cornstarch as thickener.
Thicken the chicken broth mixture.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: At least triple the recipe.
Makes approximately 28 cups.

title: last minute chicken
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Add Old Bay seasoning. Stir well. Mix in chicken and peas.
Spray 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish.
Top with Stove Top crumbs.
Spray crumbs with butter spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup, peas and milk in large bowl.
Add potato chips to thicken.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve with Ripple potato chips.

title: brown muscle bread
directions: Combine flours, brown sugar, salt and soda in a large bowl. Add buttermilk gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Add applesauce.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until loaves test done.
Invert onto wire rack. Slice and serve warm.
Yields 24 servings.

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add well beaten egg to fruit cocktail including juice.
Fold in the dry ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Cover with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices.
Blend well into squash.
Beat 2 eggs separately; add milk and stir well.
Blend into squash mixture.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate lined with crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then 375° for 45 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix with electric mixer for 2 or 3 minutes.
Place in long cake pan (ungreased) and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with salad dressing.
Season with onion salt and pepper.
Place on a greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs until golden yellow.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour mixture alternately with heavy cream.
Beat well.
Bake in large tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar, butter, vanilla, coconut and pineapple.
Pour into an unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it sets good.

title: stra-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thick.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil; remove from heat and add eggs, one at a time, and beat until mixture no longer sticks to sides of bowl.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: cocktail reubens
directions: Spread each slice of rye bread with a little of the salad dressing.
Top with a thin slice of corned beef.
Cover with a teaspoon of sauerkraut.
Cut each slice of cheese into 6 pieces; top appetizers.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts and appetizers are heated through. Serves 36.

title: yam fruit salad
directions: Peel yams and cube.
Toss fruit together lightly.
Add yams. Combine mayonnaise, honey and lemon juice for dressing.
Serve on crisp cabbage leaves or lettuce with dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat off of meat and cut into serving size pieces. Salt and pepper and dredge in flour. Pound flour into meat with a mallet or saucer. Fry in cooking oil browning on both sides. Remove form heat and drain off excess fat. Add tomatoes and onions to frying pan and bring to a boil. Add meat back to pan, cover and simmer about 1 hour until meat is fork tender.

title: mock chop suey casserole
directions: In a separate pan, boil the 5 cups water; add the rice.
Brown hamburger, celery and onion.
Add soup, water and soy sauce. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add noodles.
Serve over rice.

title: mock angel food cake(method:  stick)
directions: Cut bread into strips; dip in condensed milk to cover all surfaces of bread, then roll in coconut.
Toast on a stick over an open fire.
Try rolling in milk, then cocoa and sugar or cinnamon and sugar if coconut is not a favorite.

title: grandma's sweet pickle chips
directions: Wash and rinse five 16-ounce jars and their closures.
Keep jars and closures immersed in separate kettles of hot water until you are ready to use them.
Combine 1 quart of vinegar, 3/4 cup sugar, canning salt, mustard seed and cinnamon in a large, heavy enamel or stainless steel kettle.
Add cucumbers.
Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Adjust heat; simmer 5 minutes. Drain cucumbers; discard liquid but reserve cinnamon.
Combine remaining sugar and vinegar, allspice and celery seed in kettle; bring to a rolling boil over high heat.
Pack cucumbers into hot preserving jars using a wide-mouth funnel to with 1/4 inch of tops.
Add 1 cinnamon stick to each jar.
Pour hot liquid over pickles, filling to 1/4 inch of top, making sure there is enough syrup to cover pickles.
Run a thin wooden or plastic spoon handle or other nonmetallic utensil around edge of jars between food and jar to release any trapped air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims and seal. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath (212°).
Remove jars from water bath.
Cool.
Check seals.
Label and store in a cool, dark, dry shelf.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Cook until onion is done.
This is hot, but it is good on vegetables or with chips.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in covered casserole dish at 275° for 4 hours.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all together. Put in large roasting pan; cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 4 to 6 hours.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine pudding mix and milk in medium bowl.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes until very thick.
Fold in whipped topping, pineapple, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into crust. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish as desired.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Heat margarine (or butter), powdered cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling point.
Set aside.
Mix flour and sugar and add to Coca-Cola mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to batter.
The batter will be thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: caraway pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops.
Place in casserole dish and layer with onion and potatoes.
Cover with about an inch of milk and sprinkle with caraway seed.
Cover and bake approximately 1 hour.

title: macaroni corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a greased 3-quart casserole dish. Stir; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir twice while baking.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, eggs, salt, cracker crumbs and milk.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325°.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a deep rectangular baking dish, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese with lemon juice, onion and seasonings (this can be prepared a day ahead).
Spread on plate or tray; top with jar of chili sauce.
At last minute, top with crabmeat.
Garnish tray with parsley and serve with crackers of your choice.

title: flavor-meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In 9 x 5 pan, combine first 3 ingredients; mix well. Press evenly in pan. Combine brown sugar, mustard and catsup. Spoon over meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in a large pan.
Cook on low heat to boiling; cook 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from the pineapple tidbits and oranges.
In a small saucepan, combine reserved juice, water, lemon juice and pudding. Cook, stirring frequently, until thickened. Cool.
Fold the oranges, pineapple tidbits and marshmallows into cooled mixture.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill overnight.
Before serving, fold in the bananas.

title: sweet potato souffle with topping
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 1/3 stick margarine, milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased baking dish.

title: brown sugar candy
directions: Mix together in skillet.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Set skillet in cold water; whip until it starts to set.
Put in buttered pan.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate candy coating and add chocolate morsels in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Stir until coated. Pour mixture into a well-greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with candies and, if desired, coconut.

title: vegetable cassoulet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat large casserole with cooking spray. Add carrots, potatoes, onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes. Add herbs, tofu, salt if desired and beans. Add enough broth or water to cover, about 2 cups. Cover and bake 45 minutes; garnish with chopped scallions.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in a 10 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Put on bottom of casserole dish. Pour cream of chicken soup plus 1/2 can chicken broth on top of the chicken.
Mix melted margarine, flour and buttermilk in a bowl and pour on top of chicken soup mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 2 cups chicken broth on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: creamed peppered turnips
directions: Peel the turnips; cut 1/2-inch slices.
Cover with cold water in a deep pot.
Add salt; cook briskly for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain the cooking water.
Pour in the milk.
Add the pepper; return to heat for 3 to 4 minutes, but do not allow to boil.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Combine onion and remaining ingredients except brown sugar and pineapple.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-pint casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle beans with brown sugar and pineapple.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 40 minutes.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and shape into meat loaf.
Put bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: frank and kraut casserole
directions: In deep skillet brown franks and onion in margarine until onion is translucent.
Add potatoes (sliced and drained) and sauerkraut (rinsed, drained and pressed dry in colander). Sprinkle seeds over top; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat together until smooth sour cream, flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Pour over contents in skillet; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for additional 10 minutes.
Sauce should slightly thicken.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cover top with crushed crackers. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low cholesterol quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust as directed.
Spread meat in bottom of pie shell and place cheese on top of meat.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Allow to stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; set aside.
Cook onion in 1/2 stick butter. Mix cooked onion, rice, soup and Cheez Whiz in a large baking dish.
Add broccoli and mix.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted stick of margarine.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top. Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable munch
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate.
Best when left to marinate several hours.

title: bean casserole
directions: Lightly brown bacon and onions in a skillet.
Combine with rest of ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a heavy sauce pan over low heat. Stirring until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in the sugar with a wooden spoon. Whisk in the eggs and vanilla.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix fat and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook until mixture thickens.
Chop spinach and press as dry as possible and add to sauce.
Add beaten egg yolks, mustard, Worcestershire and cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold gently into mixture.
Pile into lightly buttered casserole.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini(can use turkey)
directions: In saucepan or skillet melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Add milk, half and half and bouillon cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add sherry, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms. Stir carefully.
Pour into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° or 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: mother eggers' pie crust
directions: Cut flour and lard together; add egg mixture.
Form in tiny size balls.
They freeze well.
I usually make only a half batch at a time, unless for a bake sale.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix pears and pineapples.
Bring to a boil.
Add sure gel. Bring back to a boil.
Add sugar and food coloring.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: german chocolate ice cream
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon; gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Remove from heat; blend in melted chocolate.
Blend a small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return all to pan.
Cook 1 minute.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add coconut.
Cool.
Blend in cream and chill.
Stir in nuts.
Churn freezer.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: excellent banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into Teflon or buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sucre a la creme
directions: In an 8 to 10-cup mixing bowl, mix the Eagle Brand, the brown sugar and the corn syrup.
Set microwave for 10 minutes on High and start.
After 4 minutes of cooking, stop and stir well. Repeat every 2 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil or bake potatoes until almost done; peel and slice.
Place in baking dish.
Combine margarine, sugar, salt and flour; cook over low heat until dissolved.
Add orange juice; continue cooking until thickened.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yield:
10 servings.

title: chili con carne(farm journal cookbook, circa 1959)
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in water to cover; drain.
DO NOT SEASON.
Cover with freshly drawn water and simmer until tender, or use 2 cans (6 lb., 12 oz. each) kidney beans.
Brown onion slightly in hot shortening in heavy skillet; add garlic.
Add ground beef and pork and cook until browned, stirring occasionally with fork to break up meat.
Add cooked, drained kidney beans.
Stir in tomatoes, chili powder, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours to blend flavors.
Makes 50 servings of 1 1/2 cups each.
If chili needs to be thinned, add 8 beef bouillon cubes dissolved in 2 quarts boiling water.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Place ribs in shallow pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Finish on grill, turning and basting ribs with barbecue sauce about 12 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Measure dry ingredients into small bowl.
Mix sugar, salt and mustard; add onion and juice and small amount of vinegar.
Add oil gradually, mixing well, then remaining vinegar.
Beat with mixer until well mixed.
Last, add celery seed.
A very good all-purpose dressing.

title: chicken livers with mushrooms
directions: Flour chicken livers lightly; fry in hot butter with onions, green peppers and mushrooms for about 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, eggs and seasonings.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: lowell inn crescent rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Stir remaining ingredients except half of flour into yeast.
Add rest of flour; mix until smooth.
Scrape dough from sides of bowl; cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Divide in half.
Shape as butterhorns; cover and let rise until double, 1 hour.
Brush with butter.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until rich golden brown.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: chicken baked in cream
directions: *May use skinless, boneless chicken pieces, but increase cooking time slighlty.

title: chilled melon balls(appetizer)
directions: Boil sugar, water and mint 4 minutes.
Add lime juice and cool.
Pour over melon balls and chill until serving time.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Mix rice, celery, onion, butter, soups and cheese. Fold in broccoli and place in buttered casserole. Sprinkle a little cheese on top, then add almonds on top of cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until it's brown and bubbly.

title: zucchini-nut loaf
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat together sugar, egg and zucchini.
Add oil and lemon zest.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts. Turn batter into a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Take out.
Cool thoroughly and wrap.
Best if stored overnight before slicing.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and butter; set aside.
Beat eggs and mix everything together.
Add to corn meal mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat the remaining ingredients together.
Pour over top of first mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar, molasses and oil.
Add dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Add boiling water and stir in. Bake in 10 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine corn, cabbage, onions and peppers.
In a bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process in a boiling-water bath for 10 minutes.
Let stand for at least 1 week to blend flavors.
Yields about 14 jars (12 ounces each).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Arrange oven racks to middle and lower third of oven.
Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Divide asparagus and spread on two jelly-roll pans.
Toss each with 1 tablespoon oil and salt.
Roast 10 minutes. Switch pans between racks and roast 10 minutes more until stalks are tender.
Sprinkle top with cheese if desired and pepper.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by a teaspoonful on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: spicy red spinach lasagna
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic in drippings and oil until tender.
Add next 7 ingredients.
In bowl, mix Ricotta, Swiss and egg.
Pour 1 cup sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Layer 4 noodles, 1/2 cheese mix and half the remaining sauce; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with Parmesan and parsley.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Serve warm with potato chips.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Combine milk, water and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and liquid alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter.
Pour into greased pans and bake in moderate 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread filling between layers and cover top and sides with divinity icing.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: peach sauce(for cake & ice cream)
directions: Drain peaches and save 1 1/4 cup syrup; add water if needed to make 1 1/4 cup.
Coarsely chop peaches.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Add reserved syrup.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbling, about 4 or 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice, butter and chopped peaches.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator; do not stir until time to serve. Serve over ice cream, pound cake, waffles, crepes, etc.
Makes 3 cups.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot with shortening.
Mix all ingredients and pour in crock-pot.
Cut several thin slices of cheese and lay on top.
Cook 3 hours on low.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Have the chopped frozen broccoli cooked, drained and placed as base in a casserole dish and add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: monkey dough bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and dip into sugar mixture.
Place coated pieces into buttered Bundt pan. Melt butter in small saucepan and mix in remaining sugar and cinnamon, pecans and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Allow to cool for 10 minutes and invert on large plate or platter.

title: shredded apple cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, soda and nutmeg.
Add half the flour mixture to butter mixture and beat well.
Gradually mix in the remaining flour, beating well after the last addition.
Fold in nuts and apples.

title: amish bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight; drain.
Add fresh water and cook slowly with the ham bone for 2 hours.
Add onion, celery salt, seasoning salt, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Remove ham bone; trim off any meat and return to pot.
Add ham bits and simmer for 1 hour.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Brown
meat
and
onion together.
Cook noodles and mix everything together.
If not juicy enough, add a little water. Cover dish and bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Dump into a pot and stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and 2 eggs. Press into a 9-inch pie pan; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients, except cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese. Pour mixture over spaghetti crust. Add cottage cheese on top, the add Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tomato juice
directions: Wash tomatoes, quarter and take hands and mash up real good. I put mine in a blender for a second or two and then run them through the sieve.
Then put juice in a large pot; add salt and sugar to taste.
Bring to a boil for about 5 minutes; then put in jars and seal.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Blend together and cook in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Have glaze ready when you take cake out of oven and pour over cake.

title: corn-okra-tomato medley
directions: Cut corn from cobs (about 4 cups).
Cook and stir okra in 1/3 cup margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium heat until tender, about 7 minutes.
Add corn and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cook uncovered until tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered until tomatoes are hot, about 3 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems and dry caps.
Chop stems into small pieces.
Mix bread crumbs, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Add to stem pieces and mix well.
Add egg whites; mix well.
Stuff mushroom caps and place in oven-proof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: In large bowl, combiner white wine Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, pineapple juice and honey.
Add the wings (whole or divided at joint) to marinade, turning to coat.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain.
Reserve marinade. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, basting often with marinade.
Sprinkle with scallion.

title: becky's egg rolls
directions: Brown ground pork; drain and add celery, onion and cabbage. Add soy sauce, black pepper and garlic powder.
Cover, cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and shrimp.
Take egg roll wrappers and lay flat with one corner toward you.
Put about 3 rounded teaspoonfuls of filling in center of egg roll wrapper.
Fold bottom corner up, slide corners toward center and roll upward.
Seal top flap with water and flour mixture.
Have about 1 to 1 1/2-inches of hot cooking oil.
Gently put egg roll in until brown on that side and turn.
Take only a few seconds on each side.
Don't overcook.

title: beef saute
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Combine reserved syrup, vinegar, ginger, pepper flakes and garlic (can use garlic powder). Add meat; marinate 30 minutes or more.
Thoroughly drain meat, reserving marinade.

title: microwave pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch strips and set aside.
Pour oil into 2-quart casserole dish, place in oven and cook on High for 30 seconds.
Add steak and garlic.
Stir and coat well.
Cook 5 minutes on Medium power, uncovered.
Stir and cook 3 minutes, covered.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Cook slowly until thickness the milk, eggs, sugar and cornstarch, stirring, while cooking, to prevent sticking, then add flavoring.
Stir good.

title: chicken chip salad
directions: Mix diced chicken, diced pepper and onion together.
Let set approximately 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup Miracle Whip.
Crush potato chips and add to chicken mixture.
Add remaining Miracle Whip; if too stiff, add extra Miracle Whip until desired texture.
Let set approximately 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes approximately six 1/2 cup servings.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, two eggs, margarine and pecans and press into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Batter will be stiff and dry.)
Mix the confectioners sugar, remaining 2 eggs, cream cheese and vanilla until smooth and pour on top of uncooked cake layer.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
If you use an 11 x 7-inch pan, bake for 45 minutes.

title: maw maw's banana pudding
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler over direct heat. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the beaten eggs, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Pour 1/2 cup of scalded milk over egg mixture, stirring to blend.
Return egg mixture to remaining milk in top of double boiler and set top in place over boiling water.
Cook, stirring, until mixture is smooth and thickened (about 6 minutes). Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pretzels.
Pour over pretzels in a long, shallow microwavable dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Cool 2 minutes and stir.
Repeat this 2 more times.
Allow to cool slightly before serving.

title: cindy's dumplings
directions: Measure Flour, Baking Powder and Salt into a bowl.
Cut in Shortening thoroughly, until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in Milk.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot meat or vegetables in boiling stew.
(Do not drop directly into liquid.)
Cooked uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes longer or until dumplings are fluffy.
Makes 8 - 10 dumplings.

title: rum glazed pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually beat in 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Combine flour and soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extracts.
Beat room temperature egg whites until foamy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on serving plate.
While warm, prick cake at 1-inch intervals with wooden pick or ice pick.
Pour Buttered Rum Glaze over cake.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Place 3 cups of ice into blender.
Add all ingredients and blend until desired consistency.
Add more ice to thicken.

title: sara's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in well-greased 8 x
9 or 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together; mix well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until well done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apples in bottom of pan.
In bowl, mix together with pastry blender, the white and brown sugar, cinnamon, flour and margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples until all of the apples are covered.
Sprinkle top of crumbs with water.
Bake 1 hour. Serve warm, topped with ice cream.

title: tuna cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1 cup boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once; stir in vigorously.	Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball
that	doesn't separate.
Remove from heat; cool slightly. Add
eggs,	one at a time, beating after each until smooth (until not
glossy).
Drop
by heaps in a tablespoon 3 inches apart
on a
greased cookie sheet.
