Bake at 400° until golden brown
and puffy, about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool and
split.
Then add
tuna fish.
(Do not make a double batch.)

title: cream tuna casserole
directions: In a frying pan cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
In a greased casserole dish combine all ingredients except paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until done.
Serves 6.

title: mystery party pizza
directions: Blend minced onion, mayonnaise, ripe olives and grated cheese.
Spread on bread rounds.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 40 little pizzas.

title: creamy lime jello
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Cool.
Beat milk until frothy.
Pour milk into cottage cheese.
Add milk and cheese to jello.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Melt fat and butter over low heat.
While it is cooling, sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; stir in sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture, fat and nuts.
Bake in a greased square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layer dip
directions: Bean dip should be your first layer.
Add avocados and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spread chopped onions to taste.
Put picante sauce on by teaspoon to cover sour cream.
Layer this with cheese.

title: billie mays corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake another 10 minutes.
(Can add peppers, chilies and etc. to taste.)

title: chiffon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl beat egg whites until frothy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until egg whites are very stiff.
Into another bowl, cream sugar, oil, egg yolks and 1/2 of milk and flavorings.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with rest of milk.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Fold in egg whites with wooden spoon.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: ultimate caramel nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease foil-lined 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Microwave chocolate squares and butter in a bowl on high 2 minutes or until butter is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: white chili
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, onions, garlic, oil and chicken broth; cook until tender.
In another pan, brown chicken. When done, add to potatoes; stir and add chili powder, Tabasco, cumin, salt, 2 cans white beans, half and half and 3/4 cup cheese. Simmer; add a little water if needed.
Serve with sour cream and grated cheese and other garnishes:
chopped green onions, sliced jalapenos, green peppers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, flour and flavoring.

title: bubble bread
directions: Put rolls in Bundt pan and add all else on top.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Let sit in pan 10 to 15 minutes before turning over on to serving plate.
Best if you let rise overnight.

title: micro-roux
directions: Put several cups of flour in a large, heavy pot and brown at 400° for about an hour, stirring every 15 minutes or so.
You may do this on top of the stove, stirring constantly for 15 minutes. Store in a jar in the cabinet.
Mix equal parts of flour and water or oil, stirring until smooth.
Add to gumbos, soups, stews or gravies.
Get the taste without the calories!

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Blend all ingredients except mushrooms.
Clean the mushrooms and remove stems. Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Sprinkle top with fine dry bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in a shallow buttered dish until hot and bubbly.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place all ingredients, except the last three, in a large kettle and simmer over low heat until potatoes are almost done.
Stir in corn and continue simmering for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add milk to desired consistency.
Turn heat off and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients all together with hand mixer.
Then put dip in refrigerator for 24 hours, covered.
Cut out center of round bread (rye or pumpernickel).
Bread shell should be about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Place dip in center of bread.
Cube bread cut from center for dipping.

title: glazed spicy nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large nonstick skillet, stirring to mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and turns a golden color, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove skillet from heat immediately and spread nuts in single layer on baking sheet and cool.
Makes 2 cups.
Store at room temperature; will keep about 2 weeks.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Melt together the cheese and milk until cheese melts.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Pour chili beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes over meat, then mix cheese mixture with the meat mixture.
Heat until hot.
Serve over nacho chips or corn chips.

title: jambalaya
directions: The rice must be boiled before you start; boil 1 3/4 cups rice and have ready cooling.
Then put in iron skillet 2 tablespoons bacon grease; fry chopped onions until edges begin to brown.
Add tomato paste or canned tomatoes, chopped green pepper, sausage and ham.
Fry, stirring well, for 15 to 20 minutes, then add boiled rice and cook slowly for almost 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to make fine crumbs.
Add sugar, margarine and orange juice concentrate.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in pecans or coconut if desired.
Chill until firm.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in a medium bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in salt, almond extract, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough for several hours.
Shape dough into small balls; place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
When cookies have cooled completely, sprinkle with more confectioners sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: low-fat chicken fingers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking sheet with Pam. Skin and debone chicken, cut into strips.
Combine flour and seasonings in a bowl.
Dip chicken in milk, then in flour mixture.
Place on sheet and bake 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 20 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender, then drain well.
In baking pan, add tuna, corn, soup, butter, milk, salt, pepper and noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add pepper, mushrooms, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. This is good frozen.

title: white christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jell-o in hot water, adding pineapple juice. When it begins to congeal, fold in whipped cream and remaining ingredients. Chill until firm. Serves 10.

title: country style potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in 2-quart microwave-proof casserole with water.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 10 to 12 minutes, or until steaming hot.
Drain.
Add milk, salt, chives and butter.
Stir carefully, then stir in Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, on 50 (Simmer) for 8 to 9 minutes or until tender.

title: curry pickles
directions: Prepare cucumbers.
Add salt and 8 cups water.
Let stand 5 hours or overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Combine curry powder, vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed; bring to a boil and pour over cukes.
Bring to a boil again and can.
Makes 4 pints.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into blender.
Blend at high speed 3 to 5 minutes.
Turn into round buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Crust and filling separate to form crust automatically.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Combine sugar and Karo and cook until it starts to bubble. Remove from stove and add peanut butter.
Gradually add cereal and spread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt in double boiler or microwave both bags of morsels.
Spread Krispies cereal.
Do not refrigerate.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds. Spread in 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan. Sprinkle with your topping choice.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Best served warm.

title: summer punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add pineapple juice, sugar, and cold water. Stir well.
Pour into container and freeze.
Set out 2 1/2 hours before serving.
Chunk up just before serving.
Add chilled gingerale.

title: sweet carrots(au natural)
directions: Cut carrots in 1/4-inch rounds, approximately 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Place carrots in heavy casserole dish with cover.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper.
Drizzle with maple syrup.

title: avo-taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Add tomato sauce, 1 can water, taco seasoning mix and olives. Place crescent rolls in long oblong pan, pressing to form crust. Sprinkle 1/2 of corn chips over bottom crust. Next, spread meat mixture, then sour cream over meat mixture. Add shredded cheese next; place remaining corn chips on top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve in squares, topped with lettuce, tomato and avocado slices.

title: pa dutch corn fritters
directions: Scrape corn off cob in bowl.
Add eggs (yolks), flour, salt and pepper.
Mix and just before frying, add egg whites.
Mix.
Fry in Crisco oil (not deep) like pancakes (not as big!).
Use about 1 1/2 tablespoons batter for 1 fritter.

title: to drink for upset stomach
directions: Beat white of an egg until frothy.
Put in glass and add lemon juice.
Fill glass with water and chipped ice.
Sweeten to taste.

title: marinated carrot salad (copper pennies)
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl; add carrots when cool.
Let stand in refrigerator (covered) overnight.

title: fish roll-ups
directions: Cheese sauce:
Melt butter in pan; stir in flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add 1/2 cup of cheese, lemon peel and juice; stir until cheese melts.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Boil mixture for 10 minutes.
Add cleaned mushrooms and boil 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake in slow 300° to 325° oven for approximately 1 hour. Makes 2 or 3 pies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts up.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until it crusts on top.
Use 2 dishes to bake dip in.

title: roast beef marinade
directions: Brown meat on all sides.
Add all ingredients except cheese and shells.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Mix seasoning (taco) according to directions. Drain well.
Add refried beans.
Put into large bowl and mix with Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, onion and Doritos.
Garnish with sour cream.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Form into small balls and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: granny's roll recipe
directions: Scald milk; add sugar and shortening and 1 teaspoon salt. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
When milk cools, add yeast and beaten egg.
Gradually add flour.
Beat until almost as stiff as biscuit dough.
Put in warm place and let double in size.
Pinch off into balls and place in greased pan and let rise double in size.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: sweet-sour slaw
directions: Place cabbage and other vegetables in a glass bowl.
Pour 1 cup sugar over top.
Mix vinegar, salt, 2 tablespoons sugar, mustard, pepper and oil in a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil. Pour over cabbage and cover immediately.
Chill for four hours. Slaw will keep up to 2 weeks refrigerated.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup until it bubbles.
Remove from heat. Add butter; add Rice Krispies, and press into well-buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chips together and spread over Rice Krispies. Cut into bars.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip, mixing well.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cut corn off of 12 ears.
Place in microwave container.
Add 1/4 stick of butter.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir corn halfway through.
Let cool and freeze.
Microwave times may vary.

title: orange delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add ice cubes.
Stir until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove unmelted ice.
Gently stir in drained orange slices and vanilla.
Fold in yogurt.
Refrigerate until firm.
(Other fruits are also good: strawberries or raspberries.)

title: dill dip
directions: Make this the day before. Excellent with fresh vegetables such as cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, slices of cucumber, green peppers and cherry tomatoes.
(I make a tray of all these vegetables, fresh, with Dill Dip in the middle.)

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and yolks until creamy.
Remove crusts from bread.
Roll paper thin and spread cheese mixture onto bread and roll.
Freeze 15 minutes. Dip bread into melted butter and then into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Cut roll in half.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Note: No-fat beans, low-fat cheese and no-fat sour cream work well.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together and let set overnight.
Take top off bread.
Tear out bread in bite-size pieces to dip.
Place dip inside shell at last minute.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine everything except carrots and onion in a saucepan and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper.
Chill overnight.
Serve cold.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with desired fruit and chill.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a lecithin-prepared baking dish. Blend-liquify all other ingredients and pour over potatoes. Cover with foil and bake 1 to 2 hours at 375°.
(Scalloped can take a long time to cook, so test for doneness.)

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup mixture.
Combine with cinnamon and nuts; set aside.

title: jean's cornbread cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, granulated sugar and light brown sugar. Add vegetable oil, vanilla and eggs. Mix well. Add chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no-roll pie dough
directions: Put milk
in oil.
Beat until cloudy.
Pour over ingredients in pie
pan.
Mix with fork.
Pat down dough to fit pie pan.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Pour water over jello and marshmallows.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Let cool. Whip the cream and add other ingredients.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: quick freezer cake
directions: Slice off top 1/4 inch of angel food cake.
With sharp knife, slice around 1/4 inch of edge interior of circle down to bottom, then slice around 1/4 inch of edge of cake.
Dig out interior of cake leaving shell.
Mix pudding and chips of interior of cake into it and stir.
Add flavoring.
Pour back into shell of cake, place top lid on and cover whole cake with Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat to taste; coat with flour, then brown in oil, turning as needed.
Add bay leaf, onion, garlic powder and water; cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Add rest of ingredients including remainder of flour. Cover and continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Use heavy stew pan or roaster.

title: sugar-free peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll dough into balls and mash with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: ground deer loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Pack firmly into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand about 5 minutes before slicing.

title: blueberry jam(sugar-free)
directions: Pour the apple juice concentrate into a saucepan.
Sprinkle with gelatin and allow to soften for several minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Bake in a covered dish at 350° for 3 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: brown baked rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in deep baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 45 minutes, or until dry.
Serves 6.
(You may triple this recipe and cook on high in microwave for about 1 hour. Serves 18-20.)

title: diet cherry 7-up float
directions: Fill any size glass 3/4 full with diet cherry 7-Up.
Add your favorite frozen yogurt.
Add berries or bananas if desired.

title: spinach lasagne ii
directions: Brown and drain beef; stir in marinara sauce, water, wine, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Boil gently uncovered for 5 minutes; set aside.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Make into logs.
Chill and dip.

title: holiday punch
directions: Beat cranberry sauce until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except soda pop.
Stir well and freeze overnight.
Place in punch bowl; add soda pop.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together except cheese and potato chips.
Put in casserole and top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Can be made ahead and frozen. Real good.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add almond extract.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Blend just to mix. Fold in lemon peel and nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake 70 minutes at 325°.

title: old german hot milk cake
directions: Put butter and milk in saucepan on low heat until butter is melted; set aside.
Beat eggs, gradually adding sugar until fluffy.
Continue to beat, adding flour and vanilla.
When well mixed, add milk and butter mixture.
Then, with beater at low, add baking powder.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.
Good with orange or coconut icing.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix boiling water, Jell-O and sherbet.
Chill.
Whip the cream; fold into Jell-O mixture.
Add oranges, pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into long casserole dish.
Set overnight.

title: cherry-pineapple ice cream
directions: Blend together in blender.
Pour into ice cream maker.
Fill to line with milk. Turn on machine. Churn until set.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together 4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with milk; mix well.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased angel food pan.

title: baked stuffed apples
directions: Core apples, then peel 1/2 way down from the top.
Place in a baking dish and fill centers with mixture of nuts, raisins or dates.
In a small saucepan, combine water, sugar and spices. Bring to a boil while stirring, then simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour over apples, then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Baste apples with the syrup 3 or 4 times during baking.
Makes six servings.

title: pauline's vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables and set aside.
Mix all ingredients of dressing mixes.
Stir vegetables into mix; set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Stir vegetables just before serving.

title: hazelnut scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in margarine with a fork until crumbly.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Combine eggs, cream or milk and liqueur.
Stir into dry mixture and combine until you have a dough.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Cut with shaped cookie cutters.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle tops with 1 tablespoon sugar and whole hazelnuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with lemon conserve.
This is a very festive breakfast bread.

title: raisin sandwich spread
directions: Cook until thick.
Take off heat and add small piece of butter. Use double boiler.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: In large pot, heat water and cubes.
When boiling, add macaroni (cook according to instructions).
Drain.
Cut ham into strips.
Layer pasta and ham in a greased pan, starting with the pasta.
In a bowl, whisk together eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until set and lightly brown on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and chilies; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; pull each apart into 2 layers.
Press 10 biscuit layers over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch (square) pan.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg. Mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat and stir in sour cream mix; spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuits on top; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: col. sanders' "kentucky" biscuits
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Nest the flour.
Add most of milk, put in shortening.
Begin squeezing the shortening and flour in the milk until thoroughly mixed.
Add rest of milk if needed and mix.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead until consistency desired; cut into biscuits.
Makes 13 biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: american cookies no eggs
directions: Cream the margarine thoroughly.
Sift flour once; measure.
Add gradually and cream together well.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Roll into small balls in floured hands and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with floured bottom of cup or glass and press edges with a fork dipped in flour. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 13 minutes or until done.
Remove and sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 6 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: spinach salad with hot vinaigrette dressing
directions: Cook olive oil, vegetable oil, vinegar, orange juice, tarragon, basil, red onion, mustard and green onion.
Bring to a boil for 15 minutes.

title: "confetti pizza"(cold vegetable pizza)
directions: Unroll and spread crescent rolls onto pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Skin and boil or bake chicken, cut up into bite size pieces. Mix soup and sour cream with chicken.
Melt margarine.
Mix crumbs and poppy seed.
Put in 1/2 of chicken.
Mix in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle over with 1/2 of the crumb mix, then the rest of chicken and top with the remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it bubbles in the middle.

title: billy's shrimp and crawfish etouffe
directions: Cut peppers, celery and onion into small pieces and saut in olive oil. Pour all the soup and Ro-Tel in a large pot and mix well. Stir in the pepper mixture and cook on medium for 20 minutes. Add the shrimp and crawfish and cook 20 to 25 more minutes. Serve over white rice.

title: okra tomato and onion souffle
directions: Saute okra and onion in oleo or oil for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and eggs (slightly beaten), salt and pepper.
Pour in well-oiled pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 or 30 minutes. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top, if desired.

title: keri's fresh fruit parfait
directions: Layer in parfait glass or tall slender glass in order as listed above.
Begin with ice cream and every other layer, ending with ice cream.

title: oatmeal strawberry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Line with foil and then butter the foil.
Mix all ingredients together except jam.
Press 2 cups of the mixture into pan.
Spread jam to within 1/4-inch of the edge.
Sprinkle the remaining crumb mixture over the top and lightly press into the jam.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to cool on a wire rack before cutting.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake according to package directions, using 3 layer cake pans.
Cool completely.
Combine Cool Whip, sour cream and powdered sugar; mix well.
Place strawberries over each layer.
Spread Cool Whip mixture over strawberries, using lots of filling.
Refrigerate.

title: rouladen
directions: Pound the rouladen meat on both sides with salt and pepper, the sides facing up.
Spread mustard on meat, place onion, bacon and pickle and then roll very tight.
Use tooth picks to keep secure and make sure the roll will not come undone.

title: tex-mex 'chiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese with the onion, chilies, Parmesan cheese and broth.
Stir in chicken and set aside. Pour chilies and tomatoes and cream in a blender container.
Add egg; cover and blend well.
Pour some of the cream mixture into a pie plate to use as a dipping sauce for the tortillas.
Dip four tortillas in sauce and place in the bottom of a 9 x 14-inch glass baking dish.
Some tortillas may be halved to fit well.
Top with 1/2 of the chicken mixture.
Layer 4 more dipped tortillas over the chicken.
Top with remaining chicken.
Top with remaining dipped tortillas.
Pour remaining cream sauce over the entire casserole. Cover with grated Jack cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into generous squares. Top with shredded lettuce and salsa, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until smooth.

title: mom's strawberry dessert
directions: Make jello per instructions.
After thickening, add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt Velveeta and jalapeno, onions and pimentos.
Mix mayonnaise and shrimp and add to cheese mixture.
Better if made 24 hours ahead of time.

title: christmas ham(griljert juleskinke)
directions: Use ham with bone in.
If not precooked, boil, covered with water, for 15 minutes.
Change water and bring to boil again.
Add remaining ingredients to the water.
Boil, covered, 45 minutes per 2 pounds.
Let cool in pan.
Remove skin and excess fat.
Spread with following glaze.

title: o'leary's beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove bacon to drain.
Add flour to grease to thicken.
Add stewed tomatoes and stir.
Add green beans and stir using juice from beans for smooth consistency.
Mix in vinegar.
Put crumbled bacon on top and heat in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until heated through.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar. Pour slowly over eggs.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° until firm (about 50 minutes). May add 1/2 cup raisins or cocoa for chocolate pudding.

title: turkey pockets
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except pitas and garnish; refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Slice each pita halfway around edge and open to form pocket.
Stuff 1/2 of turkey mixture into each pocket and garnish with alfalfa sprouts.

title: tuna fish dip
directions: Mix together and let set in refrigerator overnight, covered. Use with celery sticks, carrot sticks, raw cauliflower or crackers.

title: homemade chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut breasts into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Mix bread crumbs and cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip nuggets in melted butter and roll gently in crumbs.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: In bowl, combine all of the ingredients.
Use for sandwiches or eat on crackers.

title: ranch round steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut into serving size pieces. Slash edges to prevent curling.
Combine flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper; use to coat meat.
Reserve remaining flour mixture. In skillet, brown both sides of meat in oil, half the meat at a time.
Push meat to one side.
Stir in reserved flour mixture. Combine water and Worcestershire sauce; stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer meat in gravy 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Transfer meat to warm serving platter.
Skim excess fat from gravy; drizzle gravy over meat.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with croutons. Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Top croutons with cheese. Arrange sausage in dish.
(May be prepared night before and refrigerated.)
Beat eggs.
Mix in mustard, milk and soup.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Chop nuts and raisins in fine pieces and mix with 1 cup flour into which spices and salt have been added.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 2 cups flour, small portions at a time.
Add eggs (slightly beaten) and applesauce.
Add nut mixture to batter.
Mix soda with water and add to batter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian garden salad
directions: Cook orzo according to package; drain well.
Cool (rinse orzo with cold water).
Combine orzo, garlic, cherry tomatoes, green pepper, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper, grated cheese and salad dressing.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare pudding by directions on box. Combine pudding, cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping. Beat until smooth. Put in a clay or plastic flowerpot. Crumble up cookies and sprinkle on top. Chill. When ready to serve, decorate with artificial flowers. Takes less than 1 hour.

title: veggie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent rolls on 17 x 11 1/2-inch baking sheet.
Press to make 2 sheets of dough.
Bake 10 minutes and cool, side by side.
Mix dressing mix with softened cream cheese; slowly stir in milk to frosting consistency.
Spread on roll of dough.
Sprinkle with onion, carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Chill and cut into small squares.
Will keep 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meats and drain well.
Put cheese and sauce in crock-pot.
Add meats and slow cook until thoroughly hot.
Serve with chips of choice.

title: unstuffed cabbage for 2 people
directions: Brown the ground beef and cabbage.
Add remaining ingredients except for rice.
Cook covered for 10 minutes, then add rice and cook for 5 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: meat and mike
directions: Cook macaroni until just tender; drain.
Combine macaroni and ground ham in ovenproof baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top mixture with bread crumbs.
Pour milk slowly over all until just visible around edges of dish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or all day.

title: banana split squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs. Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken bake
directions: *If you like your food a little spicy, throw in some hot pepper cheese as well.

title: cinnamon-nut sour cream coffee cake
directions: Omit nut mixture.
Fill a 13 x 9-inch pan with batter. Sprinkle with the blueberries.
Combine the sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Sprinkle over blueberries before baking.
Bake as preceding.

title: orange salad or dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/3 cups hot water (boiling).
Add cold ginger ale.
Stir in orange sherbet and mash until dissolved.
Set in refrigerator for 3 to 5 minutes or until slightly thickened. If it's starting to jell, add fruit and return to refrigerator until firm.

title: macaroni and cheese pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Add 2 eggs and beat by hand until thoroughly mixed with macaroni and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 400° to 450°.
Remove from oven.
Add tomato sauce, shredded cheese and topping.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix milk and bourbon, a little at a time (very slow).
Add sugar gradually working into dough.
Roll in small balls.
Chill. Mix and melt semi-sweet chocolate and paraffin in double boiler. (Can just use a dipping chocolate or molding chocolate.)
Dip each bourbon ball in chocolate.
Put pecan on top of each piece.

title: achy breaky heart cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on cake mix box.
When you take out of oven, poke holes in cake and pour 1 can of sweetened condensed milk on top and let cool.
When cooled, pour caramel sauce on top and then spread whipped topping on top of caramel. Sprinkle Heath Sensations on top of whipped topping.

title: celery salmon souffle
directions: Drain salmon; season and mash with a fork.
Stir in celery soup and heat.
Remove from heat and add egg yolks one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.
Put casserole in pan of water while baking.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Serve over ice cream.

title: yankee bean chowder
directions: Wash the beans and soak overnight in 1 quart of water.
Cook all ingredients until tender, then add milk and reheat.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
When ready to serve, add 5 cents worth of peanuts.
Mix with mayonnaise.

title: one bowl fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and condensed milk in a large bowl 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir until completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: stuffed flounder fillets
directions: Place the oil in a medium-size skillet.
Turn the heat to 100°.
Add the mushrooms.
Cook over low heat until any moisture the mushrooms release has evaporated.
Stir the spinach into the pan and continue to cook, stirring constantly, until the spinach is wilted.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle Feta cheese over the spinach mixture and stir together.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix mayonnaise and soup, thinning with 1/4 cup water.
Layer, starting with broccoli and top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: steak fingers
directions: Cut steak into
narrow strips.
Salt and pepper strips. Pour buttermilk over steak and let stand for 20 to 25 minutes. Roll in flour.
Fry in
hot
fat
in
a frying pan over medium heat.

title: london cheese roll
directions: Note:
May be prepared ahead of time.

title: orange butter cake
directions: Combine first 12 ingredients in large bowl.
Using electric mixer, beat on low speed until blended.
Beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: people puppy chow
directions: In a large pan, using low heat, melt the morsels and peanut butter.
Stir constantly, until runny.
Add box of Crispix and stir until all are coated.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in squeezed spinach and chopped water chestnuts.
Chill.

title: marcella's potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water. Cook until tender. Cool slightly. Peel and coarsely shred. Set aside.

title: peanut butter goodies
directions: Mix together; roll out with rolling pin on cookie sheet.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Cool.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Set aside grated cheese.
Any cheese will do.
It is according to
what you are preparing with the meal.
Swiss, cheddar or you may want to blend a couple cheeses.
Use your imagination.
Melt butter in skillet. Add flour till thick and creamy.
Add milk to make a gravy.
Sprinkle in cheese and blend till smooth and creamy.
Pour over favorite dish.
We like it over Lesueur peas, broccoli or asparagus.

title: tea concentrate
directions: Put ingredients in 1 quart cold water and
set
in warm place, 2 hours, then add to 3 quarts water.
Pour over ice and serve.

title: one-pot dinner
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat until no longer pink; drain. Add onion, celery and green pepper, cook for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil and pepper.
Stir in noodles, beans, tomatoes, water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Add dill and cottage cheese to hot potatoes.
Put into a 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with chives and dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Blend together with fork.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: roasted chestnuts
directions: Cut an "x" into flat side of chestnuts.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with salt, if needed.

title: colossal cookie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well, add chips. Spread or press into a pizza pan or large cake pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes depending on pan size and your oven. (Watch carefully.) Cookie is done when slightly brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place the breasts between sheets of wax paper and pound until approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Cut ham and cheese into equal strips and place one of each on each breast.
Sprinkle with finely chopped fresh tarragon, salt and pepper.
Roll up, enclosing the filling. Roll breasts in flour and beaten egg and bread crumbs and chill thoroughly.
Fry the breasts in about 1/2-inch of hot fat, until golden brown and tender (approximately 8 minutes).
Drain and serve.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Bring tomato sauce and water to a boil.
Add gelatin, vinegar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold(s).
Chill until set. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken with capers
directions: In a large skillet combine all ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: aunt angie's creamy potato salad
directions: Cook the salad potatoes; peel, cube and put in large bowl. Cut up scallions and add to potatoes.
Mix together sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add dill weed.
Pour cream mixture over potatoes and mix well.
Crumble yolks of hard-boiled eggs.
Put potatoes into serving bowl; top with crumbled egg yolks and chill until ready to serve.

title: oven-fried mexican chicken(diet)
directions: In large pan (non-aluminum) combine V-8 juice and hot sauce. Add chicken and marinate for 30 minutes.
Drain chicken.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray baking sheet with Pam.

title: red raspberry tea
directions: Boil the tea bags in 4 cups water.
When ready, pour into 2-quart pitcher.
Add juice and fill to top with water.
Serve over ice.
Sugar is optional.

title: peach mess
directions: Spread peaches in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Cut butter in chunks and spread over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southwestern corn salad
directions: In a large bowl combine corn, beans, green pepper, green onion and chicken.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat oleo until creamy; beat in cream and sugar until smooth. Spread in pie shell.
Slice banana; chop pineapple and pat dry with paper towels.
Arrange banana and pineapple on top of cream mixture and press in firmly.
Spread Cool Whip on pie and sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate 2 hours and store in refrigerator after cutting.

title: orange carrots
directions: Steam carrots until almost tender.
Add butter, orange marmalade and dill.
Let stand 15 minutes; keep warm until serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain, reserving the liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Place broccoli, liquid and sour cream in blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into saucepan.
Add soup mix, Worcestershire and garlic.
Heat and serve.

title: lime dessert salad
directions: Mix and party jell the jello and hot water.
To the partly jelled jello, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into jello mold. Chill 8 hours.

title: chewie cake
directions: Note: Be sure to use large pan.

title: almond butter cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add salt, flour and extract. Chill dough. Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Stamp with cookie stamp or press with fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: double potato bake
directions: Prepare potatoes, reducing cooking time by 4 minutes.
Drain. Combine soup, milk, onion, parsley and pepper.
Heat soup thoroughly. Add to potatoes, mixing lightly.
Place into baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sparkling apricot pineapple punch
directions: Combine juices and water; chill.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale just before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and seasoning until well blended. Spread into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch or 7 x 10-inch dish.
Top with desired amount of shredded lettuce, cheese and tomato.
Serve as dip for tortilla chips.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place water in bowl; add dry milk and mix well.
Add sugar; mix until smooth.
Use in recipes calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put sliced bananas and vanilla wafers in 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and sour cream.
Pour over bananas and vanilla wafers. Frost with Cool Whip.
Crush 1 cup of vanilla wafers and put on top.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: Note:
I usually double the last 3 ingredients.
One-fourth cup doesn't cover a 9-inch pie very well.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place meat in greased casserole. Mix soup together and pour over meat.
Top with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies - cut out
directions: Beat butter and shortening.
Mix with electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add half of flour, all of sugar, egg, milk, baking powder, vanilla and salt. Beat until mixed.
Beat or stir in remaining flour.
Divide dough in half.
Cover.
Chill about 3 hours or until easy to handle. Roll each half of dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Using a 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter, cut dough into desired shape.
Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes, or until done.
Cool on sheet.
Makes about 42 cookies.

title: apricot jello
directions: Add cold water and hot water to jello.
Let this set after adding pineapple and jello.
Then cook sugar, flour, butter and pineapple juice until thick.
Then add to this the cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put this on top of jello.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture onto bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop finely.
In a skillet, saute mushroom stems and onions in a small amount of butter.
Add bread cubes, garlic salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; toss. Stir in beaten egg.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Spray a glass pie plate with Pam.
Microwave for 8 minutes.
Turn; cook until mushrooms are done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Drain asparagus. Use liquid from asparagus together with milk to make 2 cups.
Add to butter and flour mixture.
Cook over low heat until slightly thick and creamy, stirring constantly.
Grease casserole dish. Use half of the asparagus and 2 boiled eggs, sliced.
Layer and top with cheese.
Cover with sauce.
Repeat.
Add bread crumbs and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken scaloppine with mushrooms
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch pieces. Dust with 1/3 cup flour.
In medium skillet, heat oil; cook chicken 2 minutes on each side.
Remove.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
In small bowl, slowly stir broth into 1 tablespoon flour until smooth.
Add to skillet with tomatoes and juice, wine, salt, seasoning and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 4 minutes.
Add chicken; simmer covered 4 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta or rice.

title: chili cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Set on low and serve when heated through and warm.

title: jello pineapple rings
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple.
Leave in can.
Pour Jell-O into pineapple can.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove bottom of can.
Run knife between can and Jell-O (both ends).
Let Jell-O and pineapple slide out of can.
Slice between rings of pineapple.

title: peach 'n pineapple shake
directions: Combine peaches, pineapple juice and sugar in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Add ice cream and blend until softened.
Add milk and mix until just blended.
Pour into chilled, tall glasses.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and peach slices on straws or on long picks.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs good; add sugar and milk and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Melt butter.
Pour half in mix; save the other 1/2 of butter for pan.
Add flavoring.
Stir rice in.
In your pan, put leftover butter and a little flour.
Cook at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: everyday potato casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Layer potatoes over meat.
Add layer of green beans.
Heat celery soup and cheese enough to melt cheese.
Pour over top of casserole. Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight.

title: thanksgiving potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Place potatoes in bowl. Cut butter and cream cheese into small pieces and add to potatoes. Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream. Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Serve immediately or reheat in a buttered casserole at 300° for 20 minutes if prepared in advance.
Makes 8 portions.

title: venison marinade
directions: Boil all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour over venison; cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 days, turning meat occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade and roast as desired.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Parmesan in shallow bowl. Beat egg in another bowl.
Dip chicken in egg, then crumbs.
In large skillet, heat olive oil until hot.
Saute chicken for 5 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Remove to plate. Combine sauce, garlic, oregano and parsley.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken over sauce.
Cover loosely with foil; bake for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and top with Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes while cooking pasta.
Serve chicken and sauce over pasta.

title: taco dip
directions: In a 2-quart oblong casserole, spread a mixture of refried beans, bean dip and jalapeno peppers.
Sprinkle on Monterey Jack then Cheddar cheese.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; smooth on top of cheese.
Gently pour picante sauce over all.
(This can be made ahead up to this point.)
Spoon a layer of onions, then tomatoes and black olives.
(I often opt not to add the black olives.)
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Scald milk; add fat, salt and sugar.
Let it cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water.
Add eggs and yeast in the milk mixture. Put in cornmeal and flour and make a soft dough.
When ready to use, remove from refrigerator.
Do not knead.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.
May be done in microwave or on top of stove.

title: sweet pickle meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup catsup, onion, pickle relish, mustard and horseradish.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape mixture into 9 x 4-inch loaf and place in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread with 1/4 cup catsup and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Put into ice cream freezer and cover.
Place ice around container, cover ice with rock salt and turn on.
Ice cream is done when freezer starts to slow down, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chafing dish meat balls
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion and salt.
Roll into small balls and brown in small amount of oil.
Drain and place in chafing dish. Combine and cook over low heat grape jelly, chili sauce and lemon juice until hot.
Pour over meat balls and provide cocktail picks for spearing.

title: mounds
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and sugar; add melted margarine.
Press mixture into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chinese ginger ribs
directions: Cover ribs with cold water.
Add bay leaf, cloves and onion. Bring to a boil and simmer 40 minutes.
Make sauce with rest of ingredients.
Dip ribs in sauce while they are hot.
Coat ribs; let cool to room temperature.
After 1 hour, dab with sauce again. Bake 15 minutes at 425°; turn heat down to 325° and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half; place cut side up in baking dish. Sprinkle top with garlic salt and basil.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Add crumbs; stir constantly.
Spoon on top of tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ginny's delicious carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend dry ingredients in large bowl, then add oil.
After mixing, gradually add eggs, carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour, then spring test with a gentle touch (this is a heavy, moist cake).
Let cool 15 minutes before inverting pan to remove.
When cool, sift confectioners sugar over top or frost with
Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Melt butter.
Whip eggs until fluffy.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, melted butter and half of the Jack cheese.
At this point, add any special ingredients such as spinach, broccoli, etc.
(1 to 1 1/2 pounds).
Place the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with the remaining Jack cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
This is excellent with a green salad.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in water 8 minutes and then drain.
Stir into the cooked cabbage the flour or cornstarch, butter/margarine, milk and Velveeta cheese cubes.
Pour into deep casserole dish.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs, crushed fine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
If it appears to be too thin, you can cook it a little longer.
It will thicken as it cools down a little.
Serve it warm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat, drain. Add soup, enchilada sauce, taco sauce, chili powder, and onion; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookie apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine apples, brown sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, allspice and lemon juice.
Toss to coat apples well.
Spoon into ungreased 8-inch square pan. Using cookie dough, drop by scant teaspoonfuls evenly over apples until completely covered.
In another bowl, combine sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle evenly over cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix all
together
and put in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.
Top	with
cheese
and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: salsa
directions: Broil tomatoes and peppers for 15 minutes.
Chop onion and cilantro in fine pieces. Blend tomatoes, peppers and garlic together.
After blending, add chopped onion and cilantro and mix. Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate overnight before serving. Yields about 40 ounces.

title: fisherman's casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: hot crab meat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Blend well.
Spoon into a small ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.
Servings:

title: breakfast egg pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Unroll pizza crust, press into 10-inch round pizza pan or 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini with walnuts
directions: In
a
saucepan, mix zucchini, onion and butter.
Cook, uncovered,	over
low
heat
for
5 minutes.
Stir in wine and salt; cover and cook over low heat until zucchini is tender, 3 to 5 minutes.	Add walnuts.
Serves 4.

title: chewy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, blend all ingredients well. Spray pan with Pam, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread in prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
When smooth, add marshmallows, Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut.
Stir, covering all ingredients with chocolate.
Spread evenly on pizza pan.

title: fresh strawberry blossom tea
directions: Preheat oven to 150°.
Remove green leaves from tops of strawberries.
Spread leaves out evenly on baking pan.
Place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until leaves are dry and crumbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add bananas. Mix in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in nuts (optional).
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes more.
Enjoy.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Pumpkin mix:
Mix together and pour over cake mixture.
Into the cup of reserved cake mix, add 1/2 cup of granulated sugar, 1/2 cup of chopped nuts and 1/2 stick oleo.
Mix like crumbs and sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mee maw's chocolate chippers(sue b. king wanjura)
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: turkey-barley soup
directions: In
a large saucepan with 2
cups	of
water,
add barley.
Season to taste and
cook	about
minutes.
Brown turkey; set aside.	(Make into
balls,
seasoned
to taste and mixed with 1 egg.) When barley has	cooked for 45 minutes, add all the ingredients except turkey
and	cook until veggies are cooked lightly, about 20 minutes.	Add turkey balls and simmer for about 30 minutes.
More water may
be
added if too thick. Serve with hot corn bread.

title: zydeco beans
directions: Smash mustard seed.
Boil all ingredients together, except beans.
Simmer for five minutes, then add beans and simmer for 30 more minutes.

title: creole burger
directions: Brown meat and onion on burner.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour. Serves 4.

title: round steak roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pound steak with meat pounder or have run through tenderizer, flattening to 1/4-inch thick. Beat egg and 1 tablespoon catsup together.
Stir in crumbs and celery.
Spoon onto steak.
Bring edges of steak up and roll into long roll.
Place in baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup catsup, mustard, water and syrup; pour over steak.
Cover with bacon strips. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Slice and serve with drippings.

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix well in a blender and store in refrigerator.

title: gladys' chocolate pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
In medium heavy pan, gradually stir in milk.
Cook medium heat; stir constantly until it boils, not too hot.
Don't hurry it.
Use wooden spoon. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla. Pour in clean bowl.
Refrigerate.
Use as pudding or terrific for pies.
Approximately 3 cups pudding.

title: hors d'oeuvre a la harry's bar of florence
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut baguette into 1/2-inch slices and rub both sides in 2 tablespoons of the oil; spread on a rimmed cookie sheet.
Bake bread until nicely browned and crusty (about 10 minutes).
Rub garlic on the cooled bread slices.
In the meantime, combine the tomatoes, scallions, herbs and olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Just before serving, spoon tomato mixture on top.

title: corn quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: grilled london broil(from southern living)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large shallow container.
Mix well.
(I use large freezer bags.)
Add steak; turn to coat each side.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill, covered, over medium-hot coals 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness, basting occasionally with marinade.
Remove from grill and let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into thin slices.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown beef and onion in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 2 hours until veggies are tender.
Good with dumplings or biscuits.

title: punch
directions: Make
Jell-O
as directed on box.
Add sugar, pineapple and juice.
Freeze.
When
ready to serve, add 1 quart ginger ale. Can add orange sherbet.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Cover 1/4-inch with a solution of lime in water for 24 hours.
Rinse cucumbers well and cover with fresh water for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with vinegar, salt, sugar and pickling spice.
Soak overnight.
Then boil 40 minutes and pack and seal in jars.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl place 2 cups boiling water and 1 cup rolled oats.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add molasses, brown sugar, salt and butter.
Put into small bowl the lukewarm water and yeast. When dissolved, add the oatmeal.
Stir in flour.
Beat well and let rise until double in bulk.
Add enough flour to knead dough.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise until almost double in bulk.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, syrup, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cook until it comes to a boil. Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla in medium mixing bowl and beat well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Cook slowly over low heat.
Remove any excess fat and serve on toasted buns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Roll out crescent rolls flat into 9 x 12 pan or casserole dish. Bake at 325° until golden brown; let cool. Mix sour cream, cream cheese and dressing dry mix until smooth. Spread over crescent rolls. Sprinkle vegetables over top, then follow with crumbled bacon and cheese. Refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut up and mix together. Let set in refrigerator overnight or several hours.

title: orange cookies
directions: Grate peeling from orange.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix good, then add unbeaten eggs and orange peeling.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Beat eggs until light and thick. Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Add melted margarine or butter. Sift flour, salt, and baking powder together and add to mixture. Add dates and nuts.
Pour into greased 7x11 or 8x8 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut into bars and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: italian squash bites
directions: Place sliced yellow squash and zucchini in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Drain and let cool.
Scoop out pulp with small end of melon baller to within 1/4-inch of bottom of each shell.
Discard pulp.
Invert squash shells on paper towels.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and butter.
Beat in egg, add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry-nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish and spread undrained pineapple over bottom of pan. Add the layer of blueberries. Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over blueberries.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit layer, then drizzle melted butter on top. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Finally for a crunch glaze, sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes or until cake mix is done.
After the cake has cooked for about 25 minutes, take a spoon and cut down through the cake to the bottom of pan.
Do this in many places to permit juice to come up through the cake.
May be served with whipped topping.

title: coriander pepper pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork.
Marinate pork in mixture for 30 minutes.
Prepare medium hot coals in grill bed. Remove pork from marinade.
Place over coals; grill for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Juices should run clear and chops should be tender and juicy.

title: cranberry cluster cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat into creamed mixture the milk, egg and orange juice.
Blend in sifted ingredients.
Stir in the chopped pecans and fresh cranberries.
Drop from teaspoon about 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 275° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with cooking spray.
Add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: DO NOT GREASE COOKIE SHEET PAN.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk, eggs and bananas, then add dry ingredients.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, then 3 minutes high speed.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for layers or 45 to 50 minutes for oblong.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients until very soft.
Butter a dish, depending if you want candy thick or thin.
Press the mixture firm in a 13 x 9-inch dish. Melt chocolate bar and pour over top.
Cut into squares.

title: pizza upside-down
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion; pour off grease. Blend in pizza sauce, garlic and oregano.
Put mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
In a small bowl, mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour; pour over meat mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 30 minutes.
May add bell peppers, mushrooms, sausage or whatever.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips, then add peanut butter.
Stir. Add Rice Chex.
Be careful to not break Rice Chex; they need to stay whole.
Pour into paper bag and add powdered sugar.
Shake gently to coat.

title: double pie crust
directions: To keep pie bottom from getting mushy, brush the unbaked bottom crust of your pie with well beaten egg whites.

title: pie crust
directions: Add enough milk to egg to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill before rolling out.
Yield: 3 crusts.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash rice several times.
Saute celery, onions, pepper to taste and meat.
Add remaining ingredients to casserole and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Check at 30 minutes; add water, if necessary.

title: meaty stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick with a fork.
Bake in a 425° open for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
When cool enough to handle, slice off tops of potatoes.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.

title: chicken and casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; save broth.
Melt margarine and pour over dressing.
Mix; fluff with fork.
Put half of dressing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Break chicken into bite size pieces and place on dressing.
Mix soup (not diluted) and sour cream well.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover with rest of dressing mixture.
Pour 1 can of chicken broth over top and allow to soak in.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: turkey broccoli dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Place broccoli in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine next 5 ingredients together and spoon over broccoli.
Top with combined bread cubes and margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions and celery in fat until lightly browned.
Add seasonings and blend.
Slowly add water and tomatoes.
Cook slowly for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 5 or 10 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the following: One head lettuce (bite size pieces), chopped celery, frozen peas, chopped green pepper and sliced onions.

title: mincemeat
directions: Put beef suet and raisins through food grinder, using coarse blade.
Put citron and apples through grinder.
Combine
all in a heavy kettle and add remaining ingredients in order, except brandy.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently.
The mixture will scorch easily.
Remove from heat and stir in brandy.
Ladle into
pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headroom and process at 10 pounds pressure for 20 minutes or in a boiling water bath for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except 7-Up.
Add it last and beat well.
Bake in greased and
floured
pan,
x
9 x 2-inch, about 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove
from oven and frost with topping on hot cake.

title: creamy-style dressing
directions: Puree Ricotta in food processor or blender until very smooth. Add yogurt and vinegar; process until fully incorporated.
Remove from the processor and add seasonings as desired.
Makes approximately 1 quart; 3/4 ounce portions per serving.
Calories per serving:

title: creamy corn soup
directions: Using a sharp knife, scrape kernels from ears of raw corn, reserving any corn liquid.
In a saucepan saute onion and pepper in butter until limp.
Add corn, corn liquid and chicken broth. Cover and simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Cool to room temperature; then blend in blender until nearly smooth.
Combine egg yolks with cream and pour a little of the corn mixture into the egg mixture.
Mix together and then return egg and cream mixture to corn mixture.
Put it all back into the saucepan.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until hot. Do not boil.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lazy chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except hot water in a large bowl for 3 to 4 minutes. Carefully add hot water.
Mix one more minute. Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or in 2 round layer pans for 33 to 35 minutes or make cupcakes and bake 20 minutes. Cool, then ice.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add both sugar and butter; let butter melt. Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to oatmeal mixture.
Mix in 1/2 of the bag of chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan (9 x 13-inches).
Sprinkle remaining chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: yuletide banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together, then mix all ingredients together and beat. Bake in greased and floured loaf pans 1 hour at 350°. Serves 15.

title: crispy fish fillets(low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Soak fillets in equal parts lemon juice and water.
Combine egg whites and water in shallow dish.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in another shallow dish.
Dry fish. Sprinkle each side with flour mix.
Dip in egg whites and dredge in cornmeal.

title: lew's tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse. In large saucepan combine soup and tuna, heat enough to mix well.
Pour in a well-oiled 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover over with grated cheese.
Lightly cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: world's best brownies
directions: Melt margarine and add all other ingredients.
Spray or oil a jelly roll or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow a little more time for the smaller pan.
Use toothpick to see if it is done.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Soften and heat together tomato soup and cream cheese.
Add gelatine, dissolved in 1/2 cup hot water.
Mix until smooth.
Add finely chopped celery and onion.
Blend together well.
In the meantime, drain cans of shrimp and mash.
Mix shrimp with lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add this mixture to soup and cheese mixture. Blend well.
Pour into mold (or molds) of your choice (a copper fish mold is my favorite).
Chill for at least 3 hours before serving with your favorite crackers or party rye bread.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of pan.
Next, spread pie filling, then put remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in pan in order:
pie filling, pineapple and cake mix. Slice 2 sticks of margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until looks finished.

title: pork and bean and frito salad
directions: Cut lettuce, tomato, green onions and bell pepper.
Add grated cheese, pork and beans and dressing.
When ready to serve, toss in Fritos.
Serve.

title: tangy french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar; shake well.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: spanish turkey burgers
directions: Brown ground turkey.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on split buns as sandwich or over crusty bread as open-faced sandwich.
(Can be used as sauce for coney dogs also.)

title: mary nan's steak and potato casserole
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces and dredge with flour.
Brown on both sides in butter or margarine.
Add next 6 ingredients; pour sauce over top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stacked enchiladas
directions: Brown beef with onion; blend in flour and milk.
Stir and add chilies and salt.
Stir constantly and add tomatoes.
Keep warm. In separate skillet, heat oil; dip tortillas one by one in oil and drain on paper towels.
Place a hot tortilla in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; top with 1/4 cup beef and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Layer remaining tortillas and mixture to make a stack.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: best ever cornbread or sticks
directions: Stir meal, flour, sugar, oil, milk and salt until well mixed. Add eggs, mayonnaise and baking powder.
Stir well.
Bake in preheated 400° oven in cornstick pan or in a 350° oven in 11 x 15-inch pan for cornbread approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Don't break roll apart.
Slice whole thing in half.
Layer ham and cheese.
Put top half of rolls back on and place on foil trays.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Leave out on counter until margarine sets up again, then cover with foil and bake.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vinegar.
Put soda in buttermilk; add with flour.
Add vanilla and coloring last.
Pour into three 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: super macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare the macaroni according to the instructions on the box and set aside.
In a large skillet, saute the hamburger with the onion, salting the mixture lightly.
Cook until the onion is translucent.
Add in the frozen vegetables and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add in the macaroni, cheese packages, milk and margarine. Mix well and simmer.
Feeds a whole passel of kids quickly and effortlessly.

title: elk meatballs
directions: Mix elk meat, eggs, Italian seasoning, cheese, bread (wring out excess water), salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Add enough bread crumbs to make mixture stay together.
Form into small meatballs and slowly fry until browned.
Makes approximately 30 small meatballs.

title: macaroni salad with tuna
directions: Cook macaroni until almost fully cooked (still firm).
Run under cold water and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Mix mayonnaise with vinegar and water to thin.
Add chopped tuna, eggs, celery and onion to macaroni.
Blend in mayonnaise mixture and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
If mixture seems too dry add more mayonnaise to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with parsley.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter (set aside 1/2 amount).
Cook and mash potatoes, adding only all the cheese and 1/2 the onions.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles (3 on bottom).
Spread about 1/2 potato mixture, some onions, some melted butter.
Repeat, ending with 3 noodles on top, melted butter and remainder of onions.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients;
chill and serve.

title: almost heaven
directions: Bake as directed in 9 x 13 sheet cake. Pour pineapple and juice over hot cake. Blend pudding with milk and beat in cream cheese, a small amount at a time. Spread over pineapple. Cover with Cool Whip. Garnish with pecans or coconut if desired. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Put onion, celery and cloves in oil; saute.
Pour in 4 cans broth, tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Drain.
Blend together tomatoes, onion soup, water and reserved liquids.
Add to the chicken.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix beef, ham, 2 tablespoons catsup, onion, eggs, milk, crushed crackers, salt and pepper together.
Make into loaf and refrigerate overnight.

title: beef and macaroni dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner.
Brown the beef, along with 2 tablespoons chopped onion.
Fold in browned beef, drained tomatoes and 1/2 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or reheat on stove to serving temperature, stirring occasionally.

title: souperburgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender (use shortening in pan if necessary).
Stir to separate meat and cook until brown.
Add soup and seasonings.
Heat, stirring often. Serve on buns.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: cherry cherry balls
directions: Beat butter and brown sugar with mixer until light and fluffy. Combine flour, oats and baking soda.
Add to egg-sugar mixture, mixing until crumbly.
Spread 2/3 of the oat mixture into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down to make a firm layer.
Puree cherry pie filling in blender, food processor or mixer.
Put in medium saucepan.

title: colcannon(ireland)
directions: In a large pot, simmer the kale, covered in 2 cups of water and the oil for 10 minutes.
Drain and chop fine.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, soda, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into 3 small loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Use large pot.
Add 1 cup water and chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles one at a time (not all at once or you might have a blob!).
Cook until tender.
Add diluted cream of chicken soup and cooked pieces of chicken.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes or longer.
If soup gets too thick add more water, a little at a time, and stir.

title: best doggone chili
directions: *Any type of pepper can be substituted, including crushed red pepper, Italian hot peppers, jalapeno peppers and cherry peppers.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind and cook 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Stand for 3 hours.
Makes 1 cup.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In a large bowl, mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla and confectioners sugar with hands to form a smooth dough.
Make individual olive-size balls by rolling the mixture in palms of hands.
Place balls on cookie sheets and chill 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and shortening in the top of a double boiler over hot boiling water.
Stir with wooden spoon until smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture into a small bowl. Remove balls from refrigerator. Insert wooden toothpick into each ball and dip halfway into the chocolate.
Place coated balls back onto the prepared cookie sheets.
Chill for 30 minutes or until chocolate coating is firm. Store in plastic container in the refrigerator.
Serve chilled.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add 7-Up, pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Chill until set, then spread with the topping.

title: darlene's tuna macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, tuna, pickle, relish, eggs and green onions. Cover with French dressing and let stand overnight.
Toss with mayonnaise before serving.

title: best biscuits
directions: Put flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and nutmeg in sifter.
Sift into large bowl.
Add milk; mix well. Shape into ball.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cut biscuits small.
Use for Honeyed Ham and Biscuits on Derby Day.

title: chocolate bundles
directions: Thaw pastry 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to a 12-inch square.
Cut into 4 (6-inch) squares.
In center of each piece, place 1/4 cup chocolate and 1 tablespoon nuts.
Bring pastry corners together just above chocolate; twist and turn.
Fan out corners.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: noodle and tuna salad
directions: Pour noodles into a large bowl.
Add tuna, lettuce, tomatoes and any other of your favorite salad fixings.
Season around 1/4 cup of mayonnaise with Creole seasoning to taste; mix with your salad.
You may need to add a little more if it's still dry. Serve with crackers.
Best after being refrigerated.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook in a thick saucepan until thick. Remove from heat.
Add margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake until browned.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spicy vegetable dip
